title: breakfast pizza
directions: On floured board, roll out dough to fit a 12-inch greased round pizza pan.
Press dough against bottom and sides of pan.
Roll down edge and push seams together to form crust.
Top with sausage, cooked and drained and potatoes, thawed.
In bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Spoon over pizza.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate blender pie
directions: Beat for 1 minute on low.
Pour into pie crust or baked pie shell and refrigerate until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: wild rice and spinach casserole
directions: Cook rice as instructed on the box.
Cook spinach and let drain well.
Mix rice, spinach and undiluted soup and 3/4 of grated cheese.
Put mixture in buttered casserole and top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add milk; place over a double boiler.
Cook until mixture heavily coats spoon.
Add well-beaten egg yolks slowly.
Beat constantly.
Cook until mixture is thick and hard to stir.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Sprinkle lightly with coconut and brown to a golden brown under a broiler.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half and roll in a cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt ice cream, sugars and margarine together and pour over rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn upside-down on a cookie sheet to serve.

title: hearty healthy hotcakes
directions: In a bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, whisk egg yokes, oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Beat egg whites on high speed until soft peaks form.
Fold dry ingredients into batter. Fry on hot griddle (will take longer to cook than normal pancakes).
Yields about 12 hotcakes.

title: apple pie
directions: Add shortening to water; mix.
Add flour gradually; mix.
Add salt.
Roll out and put into a greased pie pan.
Add 1/2 of apples, peeled and pared.
Add cinnamon and butter to taste.
Put the rest of the apples on top.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes. Makes 1 pie.

title: tamale soup
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add corn, water, bouillon, chili powder, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes or more until about 30 minutes before serving.
Cut tamales into bite size chunks and add to soup.
Gently stir and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with tortillas or cornbread.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Add all ingredients and bring to boil then reduce heat and simmer.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together in a large pan.
When well blended, store in airtight containers.
Use about 1/3 cup (or to taste) to 1 cup boiling water.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Gradually stir 1/4 cup milk into flour, making a smooth paste. Stir into soup.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat until soup is thickened.
Yields 9 cups.

title: very fudgie brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom only of a square pan with shortening.
Heat margarine and 1 cup chocolate chips over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips; mix well until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in pan with a rubber scraper.
Bake until the center is set, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let brownies cool completely before cutting.
Store brownies tightly covered.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar until thick and syrupy.
Heat oven at 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Add 1/2 pineapple. Mix and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake as directed on box.
Cool.
Mix rest of pineapple into frosting.
Frost cake.

title: mock pecan (oatmeal) pie
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except nuts.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake 10 minutes at 425° and then turn oven to 375° and bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake. This makes a very large pie.
You can double the recipe and bake three 9-inch pies.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Place apples in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In small mixing bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside 1 teaspoon of mixture. Stir cornstarch and salt into remaining sugar mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over apples in dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Mixing lightly, add dry ingredients (mix together).
Stir in nuts and/or raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken barley soup
directions: In large kettle, cook chicken in water until tender. Cook broth and skim off fat. Bone the chicken and cut into bite size pieces; return to kettle along with remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for at least 1 hour or until vegetables and barley are tender. Remove bay leaf. Makes about 1 1/2 quarts or about 5 servings.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix tomatoes, onion, hot peppers and bell peppers in large container and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Mix vinegar and sugar in large pan.
Add drained tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill hot jars and seal.
Do not cook.
Add spices, if desired.
Very good in about 2 weeks.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place frozen hash browns in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine over frozen potatoes.
Mix together sour cream, onion, soup and cheese.
Spread over potatoes.
Top with cornflakes, then pour 1 stick melted margarine over topping.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion and sour cream.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan add peeled and sliced potatoes about 1 inch thick.
Spread with soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
(How much cheese depends on how cheesy you want it.)
Add cracker crumbs on top, then drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions in boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Layer in casserole with undiluted soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: alice's corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add corn and mushroom soup.
Saute pimento, onions and peppers.
Add to corn mixture. Put in casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain fruit and chop.
Mix all ingredients and let chill in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Put mixture in 2 graham cracker crusts and freeze.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, pepper, ketchup and green beans.
Stir well and heat through.
Pour into a two quart casserole dish.
Spread potatoes over the mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: special salad dressing
directions: Beat thoroughly or mix in blender.
Refrigerate.
Keep on hand to cover lettuce, cole slaw or spinach.

title: pork oriental
directions: Can use any other vegetables of your choice.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Brush both sides of the salmon steaks with the olive oil. Sprinkle on the salt and pepper.
Grill the salmon steaks with the flesh side down for 2 minutes.
Turn the steaks over and spread on a thick layer of the Spinach Pecan Pesto.
Grill fish for 2 to 4 minutes more, or until just done.
Serves 6.

title: herbed pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Dump sliced carrots, onions, garlic, cloves, celery leaves, parsley leaves and bay leaves around roast.
Pour in water and consomme; cook uncovered for 2 hours.
Baste frequently.
Before serving, put roast on platter.
Skim of fat.
Work vegetables and liquid through a sieve.
Serve on roast.

title: berry, berry punch
directions: Combine fruits, simmer about 5 minutes, strain, cool and chill. Blend lemonade and soda and mix with fruit. Serve over ice.

title: million dollar potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp.
Combine mashed pulp, 1 1/2 cups cheese, sour cream, milk, parsley, salt and pepper. Stuff shells with potato mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fried squirrel and gravy
directions: Cut squirrels into serving pieces and coat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in shortening.
Remove from pan and add 2 tablespoons of flour mixture.
Stir until absorbed and brown.
Add 1 cup water to make gravy.
Return meat to gravy and simmer until meat is tender, about 1/2 hour.

title: raisin-rice custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart casserole. In a medium bowl mix half and half, cooked rice, sugar, raisins, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into casserole.
Place casserole in a large baking pan, fill pan with boiling water to reach halfway up side of casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Carefully stir custard to distribute raisins; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple milkshake
directions: Pour pineapple in blender container.
Blend for about 1 minute.
Add powdered milk, vanilla and sweetener.
Blend 1 minute.
Add ice cubes, 4 or 5 at a time.
Chop with blender.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper. Heat oil (1/4 inch) in large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Cook chicken in oil over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes; reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are tender.
If skillet cannot be tightly covered add 1 to 2 tablespoons water.
Turn chicken to assure even cooking. Remove cover for last 5 minutes to crisp chicken.

title: mom's peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter, 1/2 cup white and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together and blend flour, baking soda and salt and gradually add to the creamed mixture.

title: no bake orange pecan balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter (softened), flour and powdered sugar and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Mix and
put half in bottom of greased pan. Spread 1/2 gallon of ice cream over mixture. Sprinkle rest over top. Freeze.

title: chocolate lust
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool completely before adding next layer.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour in oiled 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Double the recipe for a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (is a lot better).

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Cook stewed tomatoes and noodles together.
Add mushroom soup to beef mixture, then add tomatoes and noodles; add salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple crumb tart
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.

Add eggs and beat until creamy. Roll wafers and place 1/2 of crumbs in an 8-inch square pan. Place creamed mixture on top. Spread pineapple over that. Whip cream. Add nuts to it. Place this over top of pineapple. Cover with rest of crumbs.
This must stand 8 hours in refrigerator. Serves 9. Not for dieters.

title: blueberry-yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice and next 4 ingredients. Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Gently fold in blueberries.

title: cocoa banana bread
directions: In medium bowl, put flours, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
In another bowl, blend honey, egg whites, bananas, milk and vanilla.
Fold into first mixture.
Spray two loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Contains 136 calories, .6 grams fat and no cholesterol.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 3 hours.
If too much juice, drain off and bake for additional 1/2 hour.
Can be doubled very well.

title: overnight salmon casserole
directions: Place half of bread in bottom of a shallow, buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together next 5 ingredients and spread over bread cubes.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Beat eggs; add milk and soup.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together (whipping) the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Then add crushed pineapple, sweet cherries, maraschino cherries, orange sections and chopped pecans.
Mix well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon in hot grease.
Mix before using. Needs to rise in warm place.
Do not stir anymore.

title: texas biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Pour yeast and butter in dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out biscuits.
Put on greased pan and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: lobster and white wine in a fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet; add lobster.
Cook quickly over high heat for approximately 1 minute, stirring frequently. Using a slotted spoon, transfer lobster to small bowl and set aside.

title: swedish cardamon bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm beer in a large bowl.

Heat milk to warm and add to yeast; stir in sugar and salt. Gradually stir in 2 cups flour; stir the batter with a spoon for 100 strokes or more. Add melted butter, cardamon, orange rind and eggs and stir well. Gradually add remaining flour until 2 more cups have been added. If needed, add 1 more cup flour.
Dough should be soft, but not too sticky.
Turn onto board.
Let rise to twice size.
Rework the dough and form into 4 long strips.
Braid into 2 loaves.
Let raise and brush top with yolk and milk mixture.
Bake until brown.

title: chicken chili
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch pieces and cook with onion and green pepper until chicken is done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cool whip cranberry jello
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Save juice and add boiling water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel.
Chill until partially set (egg white consistency).
Fold in oranges and pineapple, then fold Cool Whip into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into a mold and chill until set.

title: hamburger pie
directions: *Combine corn meal mix and milk and water; use recipe for corn bread. Add enough liquid to mixture so it will pour easily over other ingredients.

title: good candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler. Then add peanut butter, stirring.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: fu man chew
directions: Put oil in big skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add crumbled beef.
When beef is browned, add soup, rice, bean sprouts, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
(If fixing early, stop here and finish later.)
Pour into large casserole dish and bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Then add pea pods (thawed just enough to separate).
Stir in and top with chow mein noodles.
Bake uncovered another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican meat dish
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and salt to taste.
Drain and add Ro-Tel, soup and beans.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a rectangular pan, alternate meat and shells.
First layer should be shells with last layer being meat.
Cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion, pepper and seasoning to taste.
Remove from heat.
Add rice, coarsely chopped cabbage and tomato sauce. Mix well and place in casserole dish.
Pat firmly.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix together and chill. Good with corn chips.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slobbsville stew
directions: Put in big casserole and bake for 3 1/4 hours at 300°.
For last 15 minutes, add 1 package frozen peas and parsley.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Place in 9 x 16 x 2 pan in order listed, as layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: onion-crusted chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Combine melted margarine, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken in mixture, then roll in onions until coated. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick coating. Place chicken in dish. Top with remaining crumbs and liquid.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add salt, butter and milk; cook until warm.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla; cook until thick.
Pour over bananas and wafers in bowl.
Add beaten egg whites on top and let brown just a little.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until onion is cooked.
Add broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Stir until well mixed and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill several hours before serving.

title: tomato pie
directions: Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on pie crust and brown according to directions.
Peel and slice tomatoes into thick slices.
Alternate tomatoes and onions, sprinkling seasonings.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise; put on top of tomato slices.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut green tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices; set aside. Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Lightly coat tomatoes on both sides with flour mixture.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add the following dressing to the salad right before serving.
It does not keep well, so use right away.

title: cheese sausage
directions: Cut sausage links into 1-inch lengths. Blend cheese with butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well. Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each sausage, covering it completely. Arrange on ungreased baking sheet. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in bowl and add boiling water. Let stand.
Mix last 4 ingredients and stir in date mixture, blending evenly.
Pour into buttered bread pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until done.

title: dietetic jelly
directions: Soften gelatin in fruit juice in heavy pot.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and Sugar Twin; mix well.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars; seal.
Jelly must be stored in refrigerator to jell.
(One tablespoon of dietetic jelly may be used as a free choice.)

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the night before.
Makes a good fruit salad dressing, too.

title: pink lemonade pie(low-fat recipe)
directions: Place evaporated milk in a plastic bowl in freezer just until ice crystals begin to form around edges.
Let gelatin and water stand in a large glass measuring cup for 5 minutes for gelatin to soften.
Stir in lemonade concentrate.
Heat in small saucepan over medium-high heat (or in microwave on High for 3 minutes) to dissolve gelatin.
Set aside for 5 minutes to cool.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut; squeeze out excess liquid.
Line a 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish with aluminum foil; spray or wipe foil with cooking oil.
Arrange chicken in dish.
Spread sauerkraut over and around chicken.
Top with cheese slices.
Pour dressing over all.
Cover and seal dish with foil.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
(Cooking time may vary with size and thickness of chicken pieces.) Remove foil carefully, first lifting from far side of dish to release steam.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream and add to first mixture. Combine dry stuffing mix with margarine.
Spread half in large baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over this, then spread remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until well blended.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant in 1/4 inch slices.
Boil until partly tender. In a large casserole dish put a layer of eggplant and a layer of tomatoes.
Fill in spaces with chopped bell peppers and onions. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt, sugar and Accent.
Top with a layer of sliced Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup and rest of ingredients (except water). Mix thoroughly.
Shape into patties.
Place in shallow dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Very pretty in deep glass bowl.

title: cherry-pineapple cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Pour in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll into bite-size balls.
Fry in about 1/2-inch oil.
Drain and place in baking dishes, about 2-inches deep.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use Italian dressing or mayonnaise with a little mustard mixed in.
Yellow squash may be used instead of or in combination with zucchini.
If using fresh mushrooms in recipe, serve the same day.

title: boiled cake
directions: Mix spices in sugar.
Put spices with 2 cups water and boil 5 minutes (boil day before).
Mix walnuts, eggs, flour, baking soda and whiskey.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat oven fries
directions: Soak potato strips in cold water (change water several times until water is no longer cloudy).
Drain potatoes well and spread them on paper towels.
Pat dry.
Remove as much surface moisture as possible.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Flip pieces occasionally to brown evenly on all sides.
When they are golden brown, serve with your favorite condiments.

title: mocha frosting(large recipe; will frost a layer cake)
directions: Mix together.
Add 3 cups (or more) powdered sugar until desired consistency for frosting.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugar, margarine, vanilla, milk and coconut. Mix well. Pour into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent dough on large cookie sheet.
Bake until brown (doesn't take long).
Cool.
After dough is cool, spread cream cheese mixture (mix cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, dill seed and onion powder together) on crescent dough.
Add the finely chopped vegetables over the cream cheese mixture. Slice with pizza cutter and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salsa corn soup with chicken
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in a Dutch oven. Add chicken, corn, salsa and carrots. Bring to a boil again. Reduce heat to simmer and cook until carrots are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Fifteen minutes before removing from oven, sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: cappuccino ice cream torte
directions: Mix vanilla ice cream and cinnamon in a large bowl until blended.
Spread evenly over bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Spoon coffee ice cream on top; press into an even layer with back of spoon.
Cover and freeze at least 5 hours, or wrap airtight and freeze up to 1 month.
Makes 12 servings.

title: basic chili
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add onions and garlic; cook until onions are transparent.
Add herbs, salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Blend flour and water and add to mixture. Stir well and cook 20 minutes.
Add beans.
Add cayenne pepper if hot chili is desired.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, steak sauce, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine this with the macaroni in a large casserole dish.
Gently spoon mushroom soup on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave. Add crushed pineapple, 1/2 of pecans, seasoned salt, chopped peppers and onion. Mix and cover. Set in fridge several hours. Take out and form a ball on waxed paper. Cover with pecans. Refrigerate until use. Will keep a long time in fridge. Serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Break up beef in Dutch oven or kettle; add onion, garlic, green pepper and celery.
Cook, stirring frequently, until beef is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar, ajinomoto, salt, bay leaf, oregano, basil and hot sauce.
Cook over moderate heat for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans; cook 15 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into middle.

title: crab casserole - my style
directions: Add flour to butter and blend in milk until smooth.
Combine sauce with crab meat.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot, crumbs brown and cheese melted.

title: sicilian skillet chicken
directions: Flatten chicken slightly.
Coat with 2 tablespoons cheese and then flour.
In a skillet, cook chicken in oil over medium heat until done.
Remove to serving dish; keep warm.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms and onions until soft.
Add tomatoes; cook uncovered over medium heat until thickened.
Spoon over pasta or rice.
Serves 4.
Cook 25 minutes.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, blending well.
Add egg, vanilla, flour and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Beat 20 strokes, then let rest 10 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into three balls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: tabasco marinated shrimp
directions: Remove shells and veins from shrimp.
Rinse.
In a saucepan, combine beer, Tabasco, salt, mustard, vinegar, onion, honey and bitters.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 1 minute.
Add only enough cleaned shrimp as will be covered by the liquid mixture. Return the mixture to a boil and then simmer 2 to 5 minutes, depending on the size of the shrimp.
Remove shrimp from the liquid.
Add remaining shrimp and repeat the cooking procedure.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and chopped nuts well together.
Set aside.
Melt butter and remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Add flour mixture a little at a time.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together except zucchini.
Add the zucchini.
(It is more moist if you will use a food processor.)
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: old fashioned chocolate cream drops
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in next 2 ingredients. Sift together last 5 ingredients and stir in.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes in 425° oven, until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger.
(Cool and frost.)

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter and pour into pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs and pat down.
Sprinkle chips, coconut and pecans and then pour milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut.
They can be refrigerated.

title: pea salad
directions: Place all ingredients into very large bowl and toss with a vinegar and oil based salad dressing.
Chill before serving. Make 75 servings (1/2-cup per serving).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix soup, vegetables and chicken in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix milk, egg and baking mix; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden.

title: rice con queso
directions: Coat a small, nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Transfer to a large saucepan.
Add water and tomatoes, stirring well; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and chiles.
Bring to a boil.

title: arabic salad
directions: Chop finely the tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and mint leaves. Combine all of the ingredients in large bowl.
Chill to serve. Serving Size:
Preparation Time: 0:30.

title: crescent chicken bundles
directions: Mix cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon).
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of mixture. Twist and seal edges well.
Brush tops with reserved butter and sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites, reserve whites.
Beat yolks and add other ingredients.
Mix well and place in saucepan.
Cook until thick, not too thick.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: mike's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
While sauce is simmering, prepare the meat.
Brown 2-inch pieces of cubed chuck steak in a frying pan.
Brown 3 to 4-inch pieces of Italian sausage.
Add both meats to sauce and continue to simmer for another hour.
Add prepared meatballs and then simmer 1/2 hour more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat to boiling, stirring steadily. Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Fill paper-lined muffin tins with 1/4 cup of batter.
Press a peanut butter cup into the center of each until top edge is even with batter.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 24 minutes or until toothpick inserted at an angle comes out clean.
Yield:
16 cupcakes.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/4 cup flour. Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.
Cut off amount needed 2 hours before baking.
Make into rolls and place in greased pan.
Cover and let them rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: italian spinach
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° for 30-40 minutes to cook onion.
Sprinkle grated parmesan on top after baking.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy baked squash
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Empty the frozen squash into ungreased casserole.
Cut 2 tablespoons butter into pieces and dot the top of the squash with the pieces.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover.
Bake in 425° oven 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in 2 tablespoons minced onion.
Cover and bake 10 minutes.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: Cook and stir ground chuck, onion and pepper in a Dutch oven until brown or done; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, chili powder, salt, garlic salt and tomatoes with liquid.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Stir in macaroni, corn (with liquid) and olives.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with corn chips, if desired.
Makes 9 cups of soup.

title: apple-wich
directions: Cut 2 wedges from each side of apple (on either side of core). Mix all ingredients.
Spread them on the exposed parts of each apple wedge.
Now close apple.
At school, your child can open the "apple-wich" and eat each half separately.
(Apple won't turn brown since the exposed parts are spread with filling.)

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: In small bowl or blender, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
First, mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut into shapes with your favorite cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello, then cut in the circus peanuts; stir until dissolved.
Drain pineapple and use the juice to make up cold water, then put in the pineapple.
Let set until syrupy, then stir in Cool Whip, mandarin oranges and walnuts.
Let set overnight.

title: carrot nut cake
directions: Mix oil and molasses together.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Continue beating and add 5 tablespoons hot water.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to the egg mixture.
Combine the orange zest, carrots and nuts together; stir into batter.
Beat the egg whites until they stand in stiff peaks; fold in.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: alice olson's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Roll into small balls and roll each ball in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: fig newton
directions: Cut Fig Newtons.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk, stirring until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and roll in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place each piece in well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt brown sugar, margarine and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Do not cut bread; break it into pieces.

title: taco salad
directions: Put ingredients in 9 x 12-inch pan or Tupperware container. Spread container of sour cream over top.
Pour small bottle of creamy Italian over sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, mix half of salad with half a big bag of taco chips.
Have taco sauce on table to add as desired.

title: cornmeal and tapioca pudding
directions: Heat milk and tapioca until it comes to a boil.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until like cream.
Put in baking dish and bake 3/4 hour in 300° oven until like custard.

title: eagle brand milk salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: cranberry-horseradish relish
directions: Mix chopped raw cranberries with grated fresh horseradish in proportions of 2/3 cranberries with 1/3 horseradish.
Serve with wild meat.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a pot; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal; stir.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl. Bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
Pour into mixture.
Put soda in buttermilk and stir good.
Add to mixture.
Mix well. Add eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows, stirring while it melts.
Pour over Rice Krispies and stir together, working quickly.
When mixed, add chocolate chips.
Stir in quickly and pour into greased flat cake pan.
Let cool.
Cut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place in casserole dish and heat thoroughly (approximately 30 minutes) at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together.
Layer crumbled cookies, chocolate pudding, Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and crumbled cookies.

title: eel stew(green eel)
directions: Cut the eel in pieces of 4 to 5 cm each. Spice with salt, pepper, thyme and laurel.
Melt butter in a large pan. Add the chopped spices and slightly stew. Add the eel and cover with the white wine.
When cooking point is reached, put a lid on the pan. Lower the fire and let it all stew for about 15 minutes. Thicken the sauce with the egg yolks and add some lemon juice.
You can eat this delicacy either warm or cold with brown bread or chips and a pint of beer! Cheers!

title: sawmill gravy(hard time meal)
directions: Mix
flour and grease together and let brown.
Thin the mixture with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir and cook until fairly thick.

title: chinese barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into individual ribs; arrange on rack in baking pan.
Sprinkle with monosodium glutamate.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush the ribs with the mixture.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Turn ribs; brush with sauce. Bake another 30 minutes, or until ribs are browned and crisp, brushing again until all sauce has been used.
Ribs may be kept warm in oven turned to its lowest heat.
Yields 8 servings, if other main dishes are served.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: condensed milk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and blend in flour.
Mix well.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter over low heat.
Combine powdered sugar, nuts, coconut, vanilla, graham cracker crumbs and add the margarine and peanut butter to the mixture.
Mix up with hands.
Form into small balls.
Put wax and chips into double boiler and melt.
Place toothpicks into balls and dip into chocolate and wax mixture.
Lay on wax paper.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Put beans into 3-quart casserole.
In skillet, saute bacon and onions for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add molasses, mustard and catsup.
Add to beans and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water until raisins are plump; save liquid. Mix together all ingredients, except raisin liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup, then add to other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Very good soft cookie.

title: good punch
directions: Mix juices and lemonade.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: fry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix in bowl with the warm milk; add oil.
Turn out on a floured board.
Salt to 1/4-inch.
Cut in diamond shapes.
Drop in hot oil and turn in oil until crisp, golden brown.
Do not puncture while cooking; place in pan lined with paper towel.
Delicious.
Serve hot.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Serve.

title: spanish beef
directions: In casserole dish, layer cooked ground beef, noodles, and mushrooms.
Pour 1/2 can of tomato soup on this layer, then repeat this process.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 servings.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Tear off of the bone.
Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Measure out chicken broth instead of water for the stuffing.
Put celery in broth and boil for 3 minutes.
Let set 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix stuffing with celery and broth.
Pour evenly over chicken.
In a large bowl, mix all soups together with one can of broth.
Then pour evenly over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes, until hot.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and set aside.
Melt butter and stir in flour; slowly add milk to make a creamy sauce.
Gradually add chicken broth and cook until it thickens.
Add broccoli.
Slowly add grated cheese; stir until it melts.

title: fish chowder
directions: Boil water in a deep saucepan; add fish fillets and simmer, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Remove fish.
Add onions and potatoes to fish water in saucepan.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add milk, cream, butter, salt and pepper. Flake cooked fish and return to saucepan.
Heat over very low heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ann landers' meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce and mix thoroughly. Place mixture in a 10-inch glass pie plate and shape into a wreath, leaving 2-inch open area in the center.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on 70% (Medium-high) 16 to 17 minutes, rotating the dish twice during cooking.
Use a baster to remove any grease that may have collected in the bottom of the plate.
Place tomato sauce over top and microwave (uncovered) on 70%, 4 to 6 minutes, rotating dish once.
Let set 5 to 7 minutes before slicing.

title: grape sorbet
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups of the cranberry juice to boil in small saucepan.
Stir into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups juice and milk.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze 1 1/2 hours or until frozen edges.
Spoon mixture into food processor container; cover.
Process until smooth.
Pour into bowl; cover.
Freeze for 3 hours or until firm.
Spoon or scoop into dessert dishes. Store leftover sorbet in freezer.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 8 servings.

title: curry-onion dip
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serve in a pepper cup with vegetables or boiled shrimp. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: creamy tuna rice
directions: Bring water, milk, dill and salt to boil in medium saucepan on medium heat.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese is melted. Stir in Minute rice, tuna and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: skyline chili
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Mix all together ingredients together and simmer for 3 hours over low heat, stirring occasionally. Cook spaghetti and drain. Put on plate and top with chili. You may top with chopped onion or grated cheese.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in flour.
Beat in eggs.
Spread in an ungreased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with dry pudding.
Add milk and beat until thick.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
For garnish, shave chocolate on top or drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: cheesecake dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, mix first 3 ingredients. Stir in melted butter until well combined. Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining crumbs in pan. Bake 12 minutes.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix first five ingredients until well blended in large bowl. Whisk remaining ingredients until well blended.
Add oat bran mixture and stir to mix well.
Spoon 1/3 batter in cupcake paper cups or well greased pan.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Measure
flour,
baking
powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Mix thoroughly;
combine 1/2 cup milk, vanilla and oleo to dry ingredients.
Beat	until
smooth.	Stir in nuts.
Spread in a buttered 6 cup casserole.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; let stand 2 hours, then cook until rhubarb is soft.
Add jello and cook 10 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in cubes.
Place in a small bowl and add 1 tablespoon of cornstarch, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and garlic.
Let stand 1/2 hour in the refrigerator.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add cracker crumbs, then sprinkle coconut on, then chocolate chips, then nuts.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° or until brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Shred Cheddar cheese.
Combine onion, mushrooms, mushroom soup, celery soup, in large pot; bring to boil.
Add stick of butter, Sage, and Cheddar cheese.
Remove from heat.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour half of the Pepperidge Farm dressing in dish.
Melt half a stick of butter.
Pour over dressing and press into casserole dish.
Put all of the soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with the rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Shake oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potato chips); place in large greased casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips if desired. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until bubbly all over.

title: honey mustard baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, honey, mustard, salt and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour, basting with pan juices every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and golden brown.

title: honkey pidgeon
directions: Mix together and form into a loaf; place in a baking dish and surround with sauerkraut.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tofu spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach in a small amount of water only long enough to thaw; drain well.
Place eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg in blender.
While blender is on, drop tofu in 1/4 pound at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Combine tofu-egg mixture with spinach and minced onions in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: petticoat tails
directions: Blend sugar with flour.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until the mixture holds together somewhat.
Using a fork, pat into a round cake pan.
Chill overnight.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add cup of boiling water. Let cool.
Add pineapple, sugar, juices and salt.
Set in refrigerator until cold.
Fold in one half of Dream Whip which has been whipped.
Take brown crust off cake.
Break cake into bite size pieces.
Line long pan or dish with cake pieces.
Pour half of the pineapple mixture over cake.
Make another layer of cake. Pour rest of pineapple mixture over cake.
Take other half of Dream Whip and pour over top of pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until cool.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Yield:
24 pieces.

title: flash's quick apple crisp
directions: Tools you need:
9-inch pie pan, medium mixing bowl, wooden spoon, paring knife and small saucepan.

title: family peach pie
directions: Drain peach slices, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Mix sugar and flour together in saucepan; stir in syrup.
Simmer until thick. Add lemon juice, nutmeg and peaches.
Pour into pie crust; dot with butter (2 crust pie).
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bite size bacon biscuits
directions: Any other seasonings you choose can be added to taste.

title: joann's apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add to the first mixture. Fold in pecans and apples. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Brown onions and carrots in oil.
Add water and bouillon and bring to a boil.
Add cooked broccoli and noodles.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer 3 times in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 hours.
I often toss in other pizza toppings, black olives, green peppers, etc. Again whatever I have at the house.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package.
Drain and stir in margarine into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
In skillet, cook ground chuck, onions and green peppers until vegetables are tender and meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes (chopped), tomato paste, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and Karo until soft ball forms when dropped into cold water; should be bubbling slowly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Pour into greased pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: meat and cheese pie(appetizer)
directions: Line pie plate with 3 squares of crescent roll dough.
Save remaining square for strips for top of pie.
In a large bowl, mix beaten egg, salami, cheeses and seasonings.
Place meat mixture in pie shell.
Use remaining square; cut strips and lace top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.
Enjoy.

title: jambalaya
directions: May add 1 pint fresh oysters, shucked, or 1 (10 ounce) can frozen, undrained, or diced halibut.

title: bran rolls
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water, sugar, bran and salt; stir until shortening is melted.
Set aside to cool to lukewarm. Combine yeast and 1 cup lukewarm water.
Dissolve and add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour and mix well. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or until ready to use. Dough will last in refrigerator for a week.
When ready, pinch off amount needed and place in greased baking pan.
Let rise and bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
COOL.

title: cheese bisque
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add flour to make a paste with margarine and onion.
Gradually stir in milk and liquid reserved from mushrooms, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add chicken broth and continue cooking and stirring just until boiling.
Stir in cooked potato and mushrooms.
Heat through and remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: cinnamon raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and raisins.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: quick beef stew
directions: If using fresh beef, put 1 tablespoon of oil in pan.
Add beef and fry until brown.
Add mushroom gravy and a couple cans or jars of water.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Bring to a boil, then simmer while preparing veggies.
Add and simmer until done.
If using leftover beef, skip the frying step.
Serve with warm French bread.
tags: Italian seasoning and any favorite seasoning you like

title: fried pecans
directions: Heat cooking oil in a deep fryer to 375°.
Place pecans in fry basket and put in hot oil.
Remove pecans when they just begin to turn brown.
(This will take 3 to 5 minutes.)
The pecans will continue to cook once they are removed from oil.
Salt while hot. These are delicious!

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Half cook ziti; drain and put in baking dish.
Cut tomatoes and warm over low heat.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Pour over ziti.
Warm milk and add to ziti; mix well.
Add cheese and mix. Place cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Remove fat and add soup bone, water, tomato, onions and seasonings.
Cook, covered, for 2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and taco seasoning (in envelope). Drain off grease.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix lettuce, diced tomato and cheese as you would for any tossed salad.
Add ground beef mixture.
Break Doritos into smaller pieces, then add whole jar of salsa.
Toss until blended.
Serve right away is best.
Add extra taco sauce and scoop of sour cream as desired to each serving.

title: sterling crackers(party snacks)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand, covered (airtight), for 2 to 3 days. Shake often.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May add chocolate chips, chopped nuts or M&M's candy.
I use a 1/3-cup measuring cup and shape cookie dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cookies should set on pan for about 5 minutes or more before removing to cooling rack.

title: biscuit melt
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin tins, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 1/2 stick of oleo and velveeta cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crush crackers and add 1/2 stick oleo;
sprinkle over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: walker's corn delight
directions: Drain whole kernel corn can (1 can).
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate chip cookies(recipe doubled)
directions: Cream
together the sugars and shortening until smooth. Add eggs
and
vanilla, beating until creamy.
Combine flour, salt, soda
and oatmeal; stir gradually into creamed mixture. Add
chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie	sheet. Bake
at
350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a large batch.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown and drain ground beef and medium onion.
In large bowl, combine finely chopped lettuce, finely chopped pepper, onion, celery, tomato, ripe olives and salad olives.
Add kidney beans.
Add cooled and drained meat mixture.
Crush the Doritos chips and sprinkle over top.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Measure rice from package and spread in even layer on bottom.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture over rice; dot with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Next, mix ground beef with onion and spread over rice. Repeat flour mixture and butter as directed.
Make a layer of the tomatoes, including liquid, repeat flour mixture and butter, spread corn on top and dot with remaining butter.
Cover and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and pour half into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees. Melt caramels and milk. When cake is baked 10 minutes, take out and pour caramel mixture over cake.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake mixture on top of this.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: blackened drum
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Dip 1-inch thick drum fillets in melted sweet cream butter and sprinkle with the seasoning mixture, then drop into very hot cast-iron skillet.
Cooking time is only 3 to 4 minutes per side; thinner fillets require less time.
(A tablespoon of butter may be added to skillet just before the seasoned fish to prevent sticking.)

title: crock pot spinach casserole
directions: Grease crock pot with margarine or PAM.
Combine all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Stir.
Cook on low for 3 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan and 1 round cake pan. Mix all ingredients. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into ring or flat dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: mama's jelly rolls
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs well, then add sugar and sweet milk. Mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to the other mixture along with vanilla. Spread very thin on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes. Turn out on sugared wax paper. Spread at once with plum or grape jelly and roll into a roll.
Any tart jelly will work.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add milk.
Pour mixture into the melted butter.
Spoon fruit over top. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix fruit with sugar and butter and cook if using fresh fruit.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until lemony; add sugar and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until set, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: plain good roasted pecans
directions: Remove any pumpkin membrane from seeds and rinse the seeds well. Make a brine of water and salt, about a six to one concentration and add seeds. Let soak overnight.
Preheat oven to 225°.
Drain and roast the seeds on a cookie sheet about 1 hour, stirring several times, until the seeds are dried and salty white.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming thoroughly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add vanilla to mixture, then add flour, mixing well after each addition. Drop by teaspoons at least 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Decorate, if desired, with sprinkles.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown and crisp.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 100 cookies.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pudding mix until smooth.
Add well drained mandarin oranges and drained fruit cocktail.
Mix well and chill.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: baked stuffed fillets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter. Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender. Remove from heat and stir in parsley, sage, bread and cheese.
Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper. Spoon some stuffing over each fillet. Roll up and secure with toothpick. Place in buttered, shallow baking dish. Bake 30 minutes.
While baking, prepare sauce.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Do not add water to jello; use it dry. Miniature marshmallows may be added if desired.

title: corn relish
directions: Drain corn.
Reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine liquid, relish, sugar and seed in saucepan; bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add corn and pimiento; simmer 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Chill.
Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: york sensational brownie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (spray Pam).
In large bowl, stir together the butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs; stir until well blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Reserve 2 cups batter; set aside. Spread remaining batter in prepared pan.
Arrange peppermint patties in single layer over batter, about 1/2-inch apart.
Spread reserved 2 cups batter over patties.
Bake at 50 to 55 minutes, or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: nutty baklava
directions: *May substitute walnuts for Macadamia nuts.

title: rhuberry jam
directions: Mix
rhubarb
and
sugar
and
let stand 1 to 2 hours. Over medium
heat, stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, then simmer until
tender, 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello. Skim
any foam from top.
Put in sterilized jars Cool. Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or freeze up to 6 months.

title: italian blueberry cream pie
directions: Fill pie shell with blueberries.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour over berries.
Bake in a preheated hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool, then chill.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and brown sugar together in mixer. Then add vanilla and water. Core and slice apples.

title: christmas wreath candies
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in large saucepan over low heat. Stir in flavorings and food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Stir well to coat.
Shape by spoonfuls into wreaths on waxed paper with buttered hands.
Decorate with candies.

title: chocolate nut balls
directions: Melt in saucepan the chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring frequently.
Remove pan from heat.
Cool to lukewarm. Beat in egg until smooth and glossy.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 coconut.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then coat in balance of coconut.
Chill 3 hours until firm on cookie sheet in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen balls.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Melt butter in glass pan.
Flour chicken and place in melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic (however
much you like).
Bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not cover while baking.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Combine sugar, orange juice, water, flour and butter; cook 5 minutes. Pour over yams in baking dish and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted margarine.
Spread 1/2 of dough in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels and nuts on top.
Spread caramel mixture over. Place blots of remaining dough on top and spread.
Return to oven; bake for 18 minutes.
Cut and chill 30 minutes before cutting.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add all ingredients and simmer at least one hour.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Slice 1 roll of cookie dough into 12 (3/4-inch) slices and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine apple pie filling, Karo syrup and cinnamon; heat until bubbly.

title: german chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Mix everything (except stuffings and oysters) thoroughly. Stir in crumbs.
Layer stuffing and oysters.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger sausage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and
sausage, drain; add onions, tomato sauce, basil and
cooked macaroni (well drained).	Mix together.
Place 1/2 of mixture into casserole dish.
Cover with 3/4 of the cheese. Add
remainder
and
top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brunch dish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate dough.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan; form 1/2 inch up sides for crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftovers. Serves 5 to 6.

title: grape salad
directions: Blend well vanilla, sour cream, cream cheese and sugar. Pour over grapes. Keep chilled.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done. Cool in pan.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, flour, eggs, cinnamon, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add pie filling and nuts.
Stir just until mixed. Turn batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans (or 3 smaller ones).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loaves freeze well.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
You can melt the Cheez Whiz first.
Break up the broccoli in the box by hitting it on the counter a couple of times.
After mixing well, place in a casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of wine vinegar.
Chop bacon and fry.
Cool; add to potatoes.
Add chopped onion, minced garlic and chopped parsley.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup salad oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss lightly.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Place oil in an 8-inch iron skillet. Heat in 450° oven for 5 minutes. Combine cornmeal, flour, soda and sugar in a medium mixing bowl. Stir lightly beaten egg and buttermilk into dry mixture and mix just enough to moisten ingredients. Pour into hot pan; bake about 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pineapple cream dessert
directions: Beat together pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Spread on cooled cake.
Drain and squeeze juice from 1 large can of crushed pineapple.
Put on pudding layer.
Add 1 large Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour, pecans and potato chips.
Mix well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: aunt sarah's scalloped onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling water slowly and uncovered, about 1/2 hour.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook celery the same method; drain. Melt margarine or butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat very slowly.
Blend in milk.
Then stir and cook until thickened.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg. Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before filling.
If desired, reserve 2 tablespoons of the crumb mixture to sprinkle on top of filling.

title: never-fail meat loaf
directions: Toast bread, then make into crumbs.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Line 16 loaf pans with foil.
Pieces can be long enough to fold over loaves for freezing, if desired.
Divide equally and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Three strips of bacon may be placed over each loaf before baking, if desired.
Yield: 100 to 120 servings.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Spread all ingredients in bottom of baking dish in the order given.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: c.b.o's(cheese, bacon and onion on rye)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on each slice of bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix well.
A real cost saver.
Add garlic salt, if desired.

title: pickled wieners
directions: Mix and bring to a boil first 5 ingredients.
Cut wieners in half.
Drop into mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put in a jar.
Will keep.
No need to refrigerate.

title: family favorite
directions: *You may use just 1 can of soup, if desired.

title: rice and fruit
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms; cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in water and chicken bouillon cubes; heat until boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in rice, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Stir in fruit cocktail or peaches.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until fruit is hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 slices plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet.
Combine flour, salt and lemon-pepper seasoning.
Dredge chicken lightly in flour mixture.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Add lemon juice and cook 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the butter in a large iron frying pan or upside-down cake pan. Add the brown sugar and spread evenly over bottom of pan. Lay crushed pineapple in center.
(Save juice to put in sponge batter.)

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moist.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix ground meat and sausage well with your hands.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll into very small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, store in plastic bags in freezer.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and bake at 400° in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve on toothpicks with chili sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: sopa paraguay (corn bread)
directions: Combine
flour, corn meal, sugar, salt, baking powder and grated cheese
and
set
aside.
Saute
oil and onions in skillet until clear. Beat
together
eggs
and milk in small bowl.
Add onions with egg-milk mixture
to
dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Melt stick of margarine in shallow casserole.
Mix melted margarine with eggs, salt, milk and biscuit mix.
Place chilies in bottom of casserole.
Pour egg mixture over chiles.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until brown.
Before serving, garnish with red and green cherry peppers or a couple of slices of bell pepper.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a medium-size heavy skillet with tight-fitting cover, saute onion in hot oil.
Stir in rice, green pepper, chili powder, canned tomatoes and salt.
Add 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked.
Garnish with chopped tomato and green pepper (optional).
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly with hands and shape into balls.
Bake amount needed or put small balls on a cookie sheet and freeze or refrigerate.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: no crust pie
directions: Pam or oil pie pan and flour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beach bash
directions: In 10 ounce glass, pour liquor.
Add ice and juice.
Shake and enjoy.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar and pink lemonade in punch bowl.
Add ice cream, then fill punch bowl with ginger ale. Serve at once.

title: *mary's shish kabob marinade(from weber grill cookbook)
directions: This marinade can be used on a roast, steak or 1 1/2 to 2 pounds beef, cut into small pieces.
Mix together first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add other ingredients and marinate meat for at least 4 hours.
When using small pieces of beef, place on skewer and cook on a barbecue grill (the grill enhances the flavor).

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cooled margarine.
Add vinegar and vanilla; blend well.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 300°.
Increase heat to 325° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: In a bowl, soak Bran Buds in boiling water.
Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk and Bran Buds mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Fold in All-Bran; mix.
Store covered in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.	Bake at 375° in greased muffin tins 10 minutes.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, and vanilla with mixer.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes for a loaf or 30 to 35 minutes for cupcakes.

title: sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage meat; drain and place in bottom of uncooked crust.
Mix eggs, cheese, half and half, salt and pepper in bowl; pour over sausage.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then cut.

title: italian almond cookies
directions: Mix well the sugar, eggs, cloves, oil, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, tangerine skin and water.
Add flour, one cup at a time, alternating with almonds.
Mix with hands.
Divide into two large strips (approximately as long as my cookie sheet and about 4-inches wide).
Place on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg yolk and 1 teaspoon water.
Bake in a preheated 350° to 375° oven for about 20 minutes.
Slice when warm into 1-inch wide slices.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown the meat in olive oil with garlic.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until the onion is transparent.
Drain off the fat. In 2-quart casserole, combine meat mixture, chili powder, beans, tomatoes and rice.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Serves 3.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Add baking soda to tomato soup.
Mix shortening and sugar with soup.
Add flour and 1 soup can of water to mixture.
Beat well. Mix in cinnamon, dates and nuts.
Pour into cake pan and bake until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: spritz
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and almond extract. Gradually blend in flour and nutmeg.
Divide dough and color as desired.
Press out with cookie press.
Bake at 350°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cherry salad supreme(serves 12)
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; stir in pie filling.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon gelatin; stir in undrained pineapple.
Whip 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Fold into lemon mixture with 1 cup mini marshmallows. Spread atop cherry layer.
Top with 2 tablespoons chopped nuts. Chill until set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 70 balls.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well.
Spread on a round platter or flat dish with an edge.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Great with huckleberries, blueberries, etc.

title: luscious lemon cake
directions: Beat egg yolks at high speed with mixer for 4 minutes.
Set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost top, sides and between layers with Lemon Frosting.

title: chicken in a casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup uncooked rice, then sprinkle the onion soup mix.
Mix together 1 can chicken soup and 1 1/2 cups water; whisk until smooth.
Pour over chicken and rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Do not salt. May use whole chicken, cut up, or any pieces.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until dry and crispy.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: aunt helen's hot dog sauce
directions: Brown onions and chopped celery in butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, water and salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: old timey mustard pickle
directions: (Or fill 1 gallon jar with
pickles
and
use
about
1/4 of the ingredients.) The gallon can be kept in the refrigerator.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg, vanilla and milk together.
Add flour and mix well.
Form into 2 balls and let stand in refrigerator 1 hour.
Roll and bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes. Can decorate with icing or sprinkles.

title: microwave mexican cheese dip
directions: Slice Velveeta and place in a microwave-safe dish.
Add tomatoes with green chilies.
Microwave on 50% power, stirring occasionally, until all cheese is completely melted and mixture is liquid.
Add crumbled, browned, drained sausage.
Mix thoroughly. Enjoy with large round tortilla chips made for dipping.

title: three cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients, except butter and Parmesan cheese, until stiff dough forms.
Turn dough onto surface, well dusted with baking mix; gently roll in mix to coat. Shape into ball; knead 10 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter, dipped in baking mix.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen biscuits.

title: red hot jello
directions: Mix together jello, candy and hot water; boil until candy is dissolved.
Remove from heat and let cool until it begins to jell. Then add apples and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Press biscuits into muffin tin, making biscuit cups. Lightly brown meat and onion; drain off fat. Add other ingredients, except cheese. Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes. Spoon into biscuit cups and bake at 350° until slightly browned (about 20 to 25 minutes). After browned, place cheese on each cup. Melt cheese.

title: recipe for a happy heart
directions: Take love, joy and giving and mix well with care.
Add kindness and sprinkle with hope.
Warm up in the sunshine.
Serves all.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add bacon and brown, stirring with wooden spoon.
Add onion, celery and garlic and brown well. Add sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook for 10 minutes.
Add carrots, warm water and beans.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 10 minutes.
(Can be simmered longer for a fuller taste, up to 1 hour.)
Stir in pasta and boil, uncovered, until pasta is tender. Stir frequently.
Serve topped with grated cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in the order given.
Serve with lots of tortilla chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and onion in a bowl.
Mix lightly. Add egg and blend well.
Gradually add milk and blend.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube-type cake pan.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix 20 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Place pan in unheated oven.
Light oven and set on 350°.
