Bake 50 minutes or until done when tested.

title: buttered noodles with fresh tomatoes
directions: Drop the noodles into a large quantity of salted, boiling water.
Cook about 2 or 3 minutes or until tender.
Do not overcook; drain.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water to which 1 teaspoon of salt has been added. Drain. Combine all ingredients, mixing very lightly. Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam and place the ingredients in it. Top it with 1/2 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and beat.
Add flour and baking powder and beat.
Mix in the coconut.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients to make the filling.
Boil the cabbage until you can peel the leaves from the heads; drain.
Put spoonful of meat mixture on each leaf.
Roll
up, tucking in ends to make neat compact bundles.
Layer in roasting pan.
Layer sauerkraut, tomatoes and remaining pieces of cabbage on top of rolls.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours. Makes about 30 cabbage rolls.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1 x 3-inch strips. Brown in oil in a skillet. Transfer to a slow cooker. Combine soy sauce, onions, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and ginger.
Pour over steak. Cover and cook on low setting for 5 or 6 hours or until meat is tender. Add tomatoes and green peppers. Cook for 1 hour longer. Combine cold water with cornstarch to make a paste.
Stir into liquid in slow cooker and cook on high setting until thickened. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix white sugar, salt, egg, butter, milk and vanilla. Then add to sweet potatoes. Place in a greased 1-quart casserole. With a fork, mix walnuts, brown sugar, flour and butter. Place on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut French bread into 1-inch cubes.
In double boiler melt first 3 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold egg whites into cheese mixture.
Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Dip bread into cheese mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
After frozen, store in airtight container.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: peaches for fried pies
directions: Place peaches in a large container.
Pour sugar and vinegar over peaches.
Let stand overnight.
Cook 2 hours or until thick. Add cornstarch and cook until very thick.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: peanut butter swirl
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Then, mix remaining ingredients (except for candy kisses) in separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture.
Then, bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Put kisses on top as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1 cup juice.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold juice.
Place sugar, butter and beaten eggs in top of double boiler with remaining cup of juice.
Cook at simmering heat about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin and crushed pineapple.
Arrange vanilla wafers on bottom and sides of low casserole.
Pour in sugar pineapple mixture.
Chill. Decorate with whole pineapple slices and whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood vegetable spread(makes 12 servings)
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; beat in sour cream and dip mix.
On serving plate, spread cheese mixture into circle.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, top with cocktail sauce then crab meat.
Serve with assorted crackers. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets. Steam until crisp-tender. Mix soup, milk, cheese, carrots, parsley and basil. Place cauliflower into 7 x 11-inch baking dish and pour sauce over it. Place biscuit pieces around edges of dish. Bake at 350° until biscuits are nice and brown, about 15 minutes. Makes 6 generous servings.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Cook vegetables until broken apart.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: two by four
directions: Mix together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy until smooth. Set aside.
In skillet in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken until browned. Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
In skillet in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables with garlic until tender-crisp.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in reserved chicken and broth mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cook time:
20 minutes.

title: broasted potatoes
directions: Clean and peel potatoes, allowing 2 potatoes per person.
Cut in fourths.
Melt butter or margarine in baking pan.
Sprinkle Lawry's seasoned salt in melted butter.
Place potatoes in pan and coat with seasoned butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar-free butterfinger pie
directions: Freeze Slim Fast bars and crush. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 4 1/2 of the crushed Slim Fast bars. Add 4 to 5 packs artificial sweetener. Put remaining candy bars on top of pie.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. (Garnish casserole with optional canned asparagus spears and pimiento strip.)

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; debone.
Place in bottom of dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Mix dry ingredients and mix well with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Heat soup and broth to boiling point.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes own crust.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs until blended.
Place half of ingredients in layers in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer remaining half of ingredients.
Pour condensed milk over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in small squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: You will need 1 greased sheet pan.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cake mix, oil and egg on medium speed until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients. Over medium heat, cook and stir until chips melt.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: chili
directions: Cook beans as directed. Cook ground beef in pan. Add onion just before ground beef is done. Continue cooking and add tomato sauce, chili powder and ketchup. Simmer for 15 minutes. Add mixture to beans.
Bring to a boil.
Salt to taste.

title: onion cornbread
directions: Saute
onion
in
oleo until tender (about 10 minutes). Cool slightly; add sour cream, salt and half the cheese.
Set aside. Combine
mix,
egg, milk and corn.	Stir until smooth. Spread batter
in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Spoon onion mix evenly and gently
on top
of batter.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before slicing in squares.

title: chutney cheese spread
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Remove fruit from chutney, chop fine.
Add chopped fruit and chutney syrup to cheese mixture.
Stir in onions, ginger and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with sesame crackers.
Makes 1 cup.

title: jello summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill in your serving dish until firm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend all thoroughly. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: whitehall fruit fritters
directions: Pour oil into skillet or pan to depth of 1 1/2-inches.
Heat over medium heat to 350°.
Blend dry ingredients.

Stir in egg, milk and fruit. Beat until batter is smooth and thick. Drop by spoonfuls into oil. Fry until evenly brown, about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon to drain on paper towel. Dust lightly with powdered sugar.
Serve immediately.
Makes 16 to 18 fritters.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve soda in warm water; set aside.
Combine sugar, applesauce and butter, then add flour with the spices, sifted together.
Add soda and water mixture.
Last add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Bake in slow 350° oven.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut flowerets into bite size pieces. Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower and bacon in a large bowl. Combine mayonnaise mixture evenly over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover salad tightly and chill 8 hours. Toss gently before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Mix remaining ingredients separately, then combine with first mixture. Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls and coat with sugar. Bake at 350°, 2-inches apart on cookie sheet until light golden color and still a little gooey.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well; in saucepan, blend eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Gently heat stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes until well blended.
Do not boil.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread cubes on bottom, cover with grated cheese and sausage.
Spoon egg mixture on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix mushroom soup and remaining 1/2 cup of milk; pour over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 55 minutes.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine Italian dressing, vinegar and curry powder.
Add to rice mixtures and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 4 servings; about 95 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, both sugars, all spices and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for about 25 minutes or until custard is almost set but still soft in center.
Do not overbake.

title: party pizzas
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together and drain.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients except bread.
Mix together.
Spread on sliced bread.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze at least 30 minutes.
After frozen, place in Ziploc bags or Tupperware containers and return to freezer.
When ready to cook, remove the number needed and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ground beef bake
directions: Crumble ground beef into skillet.
Cook until it loses red color.
Add onions during last few minutes of cooking time. Drain off grease.
Add parsley, garlic powder, salt and pepper and vegetable soup.
Combine milk and mushroom soup, stirring until smooth.
Blend into meat mixture.
Bring to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Mix in sour cream. Transfer mixture to 3-quart size casserole.
Drop topping by tablespoonfuls over top while meat is still hot.
Bake in oven at 450° about 15 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix butter, brown sugar and syrup; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda, stirring just until mixed.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake for about 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: churros cubanos
directions: Fry in vegetable shortening.
Put milk, butter and salt to boil.
Add flour and stir quickly.
Put dough into a cookie press. Twist out dough in large concentric circles into hot fat.
Turn when brown.
Remove when both sides are brown.
Drain on paper towels.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with sugar.

title: pancake roll-ups
directions: Use any basic pancake recipe (scratch or box).
Add enough extra liquid to make batter thinner than called for.
Pour small amount of batter in a pan with a small bit of hot oil in it.
Tilt pan to let batter coat the entire bottom of pan.
Cook until batter bubbles at edges and turn.
Cook again until brown.
Serve with jam, jelly, syrup, etc. (any toppings will do).
Spread topping on pancakes and roll up.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise, sour cream and dry soup mix.
Add spinach, onions and water chestnuts.
Serve with crackers and raw vegetables.
A hollowed out loaf of bread may be used as a serving dish.

title: brush's broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and onion and pour over the raisins and broccoli.
Sprinkle on bacon.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: grilled whole filet of beef
directions: Place the meat in a large, wide dish.
Slice 2 medium onions and lightly crush the bay leaves and black peppercorns.
Put them around the filet, then add the bottle of red wine, olive oil and Italian parsley sprigs.
Marinate the filet at cool room temperature for several hours or overnight, turning it several times.

title: great grandma's doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead on floured table; roll out and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fat fry in 2
to 3-inches of vegetable oil until golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: apple strudel quick and easy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking sheet.
To prepare pastry, unfold sheets of phyllo so they lie flat.
Stack 4 sheets on plastic wrap.
Brush top sheet with butter.
Keep other sheets covered with plastic wrap and damp cloth (to keep from drying out).
Spread 1/2 pie filling on short side of phyllo.
Roll jelly roll style, using plastic wrap as guide.
Repeat with remaining sheets.
Bake until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool sheets on wire racks for 15 minutes.
Transfer to serving tray until cool. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Chop mushrooms fine and save liquid.
Work all ingredients until it sticks together.
Have heavy skillet hot and lightly greased.
Sear both sides of steak, flattening out in skillet. Pour mushroom juice over meat.
Reduce to medium-low.
Cover and cook until done.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Drain peas and asparagus.
Butter casserole dish.
Line with crumbs.
Layer peas and asparagus.
Mix milk and soup and pour over.
Top with crumbs and cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan filling
directions: In medium saucepan, combine corn syrup, evaporated milk, sugar, butter, egg yolks and vanilla, stirring frequently. Cook over medium heat until thickened, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pecans. Cool until thick enough to spread, stirring occasionally. Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: dough ornaments for christmas
directions: Put your flour and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually add your water.
Knead the dough 7 to 10 minutes, until smooth.
Then roll out and use cookie cutters or make your own shapes.
Make a small hole in the top of each ornament.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 325° until light brown.
When cool, paint.
Use colored yarn through the hole and hang.

title: for men only
directions: Pour your favorite cereal into a bowl.
Pour milk over top of cereal.
Eat with a spoon.
For best results, leave dirty dishes on table.

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir to mix well. Spoon into small ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: impossible broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and onion.
Pour into plate.
Beat milk, eggs, biscuit mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
May substitute 1 1/2 cups chicken for 1 package of broccoli.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in large baking dish. In small bowl, combine broth and hot pepper sauce; pour over chicken.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, turning once.
Remove pan from oven.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Combine all other ingredients and cook in a casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Roll out pie crust.
Cut into squares.
Mix chicken with 1/2 the soup.
Put filling in each square; fold over and seal.
Prick top with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Use remaining sauce for on top when served.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Add chips and nuts.
Mix well to evenly distribute.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed crown roast of pork
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Season meat with salt and pepper. Place meat, bone ends up, in open shallow roasting pan; wrap bone ends in aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning. To hold shape of roast, place a small ovenproof bowl or cup in crown. Insert meat thermometer so tip is in thickest part of meat and does not rest on fat or bone. Do not add water. Do not cover. Roast 30 to 35 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer registers 170°. One hour before meat is done, remove bowl from center of crown, fill crown with stuffing (8 cups for 8 pounds). Cover stuffing with foil during first 30 minutes. When roast is done, remove foil from bone ends and replace with crab apples or paper frills.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Clean cabbage and boil in water until leaves are soft (about 7 or 8 minutes).
Mix rest of ingredients together and when cabbage leaves are soft, roll balls of hamburger in leaves and place in a big pan.
Pour water to top of "pigs" and add tomato sauce.
Boil on low for 3 or 4 hours.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugars until blended, then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until well blended.
If necessary, chill dough.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add enough water to liquid from drained pineapple to make one cup.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple, cranberry-orange relish, apples, pecans and celery. Chill 24 hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings (no cholesterol).

title: bread pot fondue
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Slice off top of bread; reserve top.
Hollow out inside with small paring knife, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into 1-inch cubes; you should have about 4 cups.
Reserve for toasting.

title: rice-sausage casserole
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together; pour off most of the fat. Boil rice in water with bouillon cube and Worcestershire sauce. Combine in a casserole dish.
Crumble cornflakes and butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crescent rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and the yeast. In the saucepan, heat milk, water, sugar, salt and Crisco just until warm.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix for 1/2 minute with mixer.
Scrape down sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
By hand, stir enough flour in to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise 20 minutes. Divide dough.
Roll out.
Cut into triangles.
Roll up.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix and put in doggie buns.
Wrap in tinfoil and put in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with stuffing mix.
Put a little stuffing in bottom of pan (about 1/2).
Spread chicken on top of stuffing. Mix soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Put rest of stuffing mix on top and bake at 350° until soup gets hot, about 30 minutes.

title: golden shrimp puffs
directions: Broiled:
Sprinkle
with
salt, pepper, lemon juice and butter.
Wrap in
foil
and
place	under broiler for 10 to 12 minutes on each side.
If extra large fish, add 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter oatmeal clusters
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil for 30 seconds.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper.
Cool.

title: cranberry nut cake
directions: Grease pie pan.
Put cranberries in pie pan and cover with 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Melt oleo and add extract, sugar, flour and eggs.
Pour mixture over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake and top with powdered sugar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the butter, sugar, eggs and flavorings. Cream together.
Add the milk and flour mixture gradually, beating until well blended. Scrape the bowl as necessary. Refrigerate the dough at least 2 hours.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first 2 ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping mix.
Mix well and set aside.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange apple slices over base.
Blend sour cream and egg; spread over apples.
Sprinkle reserved topping mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 squares.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well cheese, lemon, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Next, add crab and mix well.
Place in greased dish and top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and gradually add Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well; add ginger and rind.
Beat until fluffy.
Refrigerate. Makes about 2 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients after browning meat and cooking macaroni.
Pour into Pyrex like dish.
Top with cheese.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix well. Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, water and sugar until berries stop popping. Dissolve package of lemon jello and marshmallows while mixture is hot.
Let cool.
Then add chopped apples, celery, nuts and crushed pineapple.
Chill until well set.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add to butter and egg mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood supreme(may prepare ahead.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter large casserole dish.
Combine soup and salad dressing.
Add onion and milk.
Mix thoroughly. Season with nutmeg, cayenne pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and sherry to taste.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with paprika and slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Place wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Arrange 4 pecan halves in shape of star on wax paper.
Place 1 caramel on top of every group of pecan halves.
Place in oven for 30 seconds at 350°.
Remove cookie sheet from oven.
Place one kiss on each caramel, allowing the kiss to melt into the caramel and on the pecans.
Repeat this for each group of pecans.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; cover with mushrooms.

title: savory macaroni
directions: Brown meats in skillet.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Add olives, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Mix. Stir in tomatoes, water, salt and pepper, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce.
Add macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and reduce heat.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Stir often.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes more.
You may use spaghetti or noodles in place of macaroni.

title: "buckeye" candy
directions: Blend butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Form into "buckeye" sized balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and paraffin kept hot in double boiler.
Use toothpick in center of peanut butter balls to dip, not quite covering to top to resemble buckeyes.
Later, gently smooth top to cover toothpick hole.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in oleo until crumbs are the size of peas.
Stir in egg yolks.
Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and reserve the rest. Combine apples, remaining flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Place apple mixture over crust in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with thin icing of powdered sugar and milk.

title: corn mushroom soup
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and saute until nearly crisp. Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons of drippings and saute onion in these drippings.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Heat until almost boiling. Serve with a garnish of parsley.
Serves 4.

title: banana fritters
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and baking powder. In another bowl, beat together eggs, milk, mashed banana and vanilla.
Stir liquid ingredients all at once into flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Let batter sit for 30 minutes.
Pour oil into large saucepan to half full and heat over medium heat.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook 5 minutes or until golden brown.
To serve, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 20 fritters.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add can of tomatoes with green chili sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer until it thickens.
Add this to baking pan and let cool completely.
Then add layers as follows:
sour cream, diced tomatoes, shredded Monterey Jack cheese, shredded Cheddar cheese, scallions, black olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Enjoy!

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In saucepan, put butter or margarine, salt, flour and milk. Be sure to keep this smooth; I use a wire whisk.
Add cheese. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, rice, onion and 1 can tomato sauce.
Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water for 4 minutes; drain.
Place portion of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll up, folding over ends.
Place side seam down in skillet.
Mix remaining tomato sauce with brown sugar and pour over rolls.
Simmer, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste often. Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Cream the cheese with sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Slice 1 package dough and layer on bottom of Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cheese mixture on dough.
Slice the second package and place over cheese layer.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: party cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
In another bowl sift flour baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to the sugar and egg mixture.
Blend well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's; save the rest for decorating.
Drop by rounded tsp. two inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with remaining M&M's.
Bake on center rack at 375 degrees for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cat's picadillo
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease. Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender.
Serve with Mexicali corn and warm tortillas.
Serves approximately 4.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water, then mix other ingredients.

title: freezer dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, yeast and powdered milk. Combine water and margarine in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until liquid reaches 120°.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Beat in eggs and 1/2 cup flour. Continue beating in flour to make soft dough. Turn out onto floured board.
Knead until smooth. Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel, for 20 minutes.
Punch down dough. Shape as desired. Place on greased baking sheet. Cover with plastic wrap and freeze. Remove from freezer as desired.
Place on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well for up to 4 weeks.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with utility fork.
Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut in pan.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 minute.
Spoon over cake.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into the topping and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill overnight.
Store leftover cake in refrigerator.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and mix with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with pie filling.

title: glazed raisins cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes.
Turn onto cloth covered board well dusted with Bisquick.
Gently roll to coat.
Shape into balls; knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter dipped in oil or baking mix.
Bake at 450° on greased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Trim excess fat from pork.
Cut pork diagonally into very thin strips.
Grease lightly a 10-inch skillet.
Fry pork until brown. Stir in bouillon, celery, onion and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Shake reserved mushroom liquid and the cornstarch in tightly covered container; stir gradually into pork.
Add mushrooms, Chinese vegetables and gravy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 5.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and pour into dish.
On top, spoon on 1 large can any flavor pie filling.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown on top. Serve with ice cream.

title: cranberry marble salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in pineapple. Chill mixture until it is slightly thickened. Stir in cranberry sauce. Alternate layers of gelatin mixture and sour cream in mold, drawing a spatula through it to create a marbleized appearance. Refrigerate. Serves 10-12.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's candy.
Use remaining candies for decorating.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Decorate tops. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix white sugar and brown sugar with butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
When cool, break into pieces. Drain pineapple thoroughly (save the juice).
Slice bananas into the pineapple juice.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Using a punch bowl or a large bowl of your choice, put layer of broken cake on bottom, then pudding, pie filling, pineapple (well drained), bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: sliced turkey breast
directions: Flour sliced turkey breast and brown in small amount of oil. Layer in baking dish with Prego spaghetti sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese (grated or sliced).
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: honey roasted bridge mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Combine honey, butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Pour honey mixture over nuts and toss until nuts are coated.
Spread on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until nuts are glazed and lightly browned. Do not allow to burn.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from foil. Combine sugar and rest of cinnamon.
Toss with glazed nuts to coat.

title: colonel's kentucky slaw
directions: Toss cabbage lightly with sugar and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drench it all in milk.
Cover and refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes.

title: japanese salad
directions: Cook saifun in boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes or longer. Drain and set aside.
Add clams, shredded lettuce and sliced cucumber, celery and carrots.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Cut crosswise in half.
Place in deep bowl, sprinkling each layer with seasoning and herbs.
Combine oil and vinegar.
Pour over tomatoes, tilting bowl so all tomatoes are covered.
Cover.
Chill an hour or so, occasionally spooning dressing over tomatoes.
Drain off excess dressing and arrange tomato halves on a platter.
Serves 6.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for about 30 to 45 seconds. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1 small can coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pork chops with sage onions
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with flour.
Brown on both sides in skillet with 2 tablespoons of oil.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove chops.
Put 5 cups of sliced onion in skillet and cook until lightly browned.
Add salt, pepper, sage and water.
Arrange chops on top of onion.
Cover and simmer for about 1/2 hour or until chops are tender.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
With mixer, beat margarine until smooth.
Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate one hour.

title: speckled chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Line bottom with waxed paper or parchment paper and lightly grease the paper.
Set aside.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan, spread rice.
Place chicken on rice.
Pour soup and consomme over chicken.
Sprinkle soup mix on top.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Line pie pan with unbaked pie crust.
Dump can of crushed pineapple into pie pan, leaving 1 inch of pineapple juice in can. Add cornstarch and sugar to juice and stir.
Pour over pineapple in pie pan.
Add pats of butter.
Add top crust.
Bake at 350° until top crust is brown.
Yum.
Very easy, scrumptious.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onions in margarine until they are translucent but not yet beginning to brown.
Add water and all spices.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.
Under the broiler, toast the bread on both sides.
Put log of cheese in the bottom of each bowl. Ladle the soup into the bowls.
Float 1 piece of bread in each bowl.
Garnish each piece of toast with 1 ounce of cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mix.
Chill dough for a few hours or overnight.
Roll into flattened 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: alabama yams
directions: Whip the sweet potatoes.
Add the butter, sugar, brown sugar, coconut and eggs.
Top with cornflakes, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Bake 30 minutes to warm at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and oil. Pour in greased iron skillet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: boston baked beans
directions: On Friday night, put the beans to soak in a kettle full of cold water.
In the morning, pour the water off, cover with fresh water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until you can blow the skins off.
To do this take a spoonful of the beans from the pot.
(If you should get your face down in the steam you might get badly burned.)

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes, adding rest of ingredients.
Whip together; put in a buttered casserole dish.
Set in refrigerator overnight (a couple of days doesn't matter).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together; add enough milk to make it thick enough to make about 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook in deep fat until done.

title: green bean and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add flour; cook until smooth.
Transfer to double boiler; add milk and light cream. Stir over boiling water until thickened.
Add cheese, hot pepper sauce, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: tanzania chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and stew, keeping meat on bones.
Mix together all remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and simmer together. Thicken a bit with cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: mary lou's cookies
directions: Blend butter, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: green beans with swiss cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter and blend in flour and pepper; cook, stirring until bubbling.
Blend in milk.
Remove and stir in onion and sour cream.
Combine sauce with green beans and cheese. Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix and let congeal.

title: green rice
directions: Heat broccoli until thawed; saute onion in butter.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Separate egg and beat egg white until stiff.
Add egg yolk to sifted flour, baking powder and salt. Add mixture with milk and vanilla.
Fold in egg white and berries. Bake in 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jimmy's easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box, drain.
Stir in soup and chicken.
Good hot or cold.

title: quantity pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together in large bowl (Tupperware with lid).
Add shortening.
Blend with dry mixture.
Store in tight container.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise.
Flake chicken and mix with celery, onions, sliced water chestnuts, diced eggs and 1/2 of chips.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with balance of chips.
Can be prepared day before and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar add eggs.
Add remainder of ingredients and last fold in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° in 10-inch casserole for 1 hour.

title: pickled wieners
directions: Pack wieners, onions and peppers in a gallon jar.
Heat vinegar and spices and pour over wieners.
Keep out of refrigerator.
These will keep indefinitely.
Good to take on camping trips.

title: meme's chicken pot pie
directions: Season and boil whole chicken; debone.
In a large black skillet, use chicken broth thickened with flour (in small amount of cold water to prevent lumps).
Cut up 4 to 5 hard-boiled eggs and add them to the chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Put soup in bowls.
Add toasted garlic bread.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and add grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Brown in oven.

title: "b's butt"
directions: Chill and pour in martini glass.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Fill paper liners in cupcake pans 2/3 full with mix.
Mix cream cheese with egg, sugar and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: date orange bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine egg, water and 1/2 cup orange juice.
Add bread mix and oats.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn mixture into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: stuffed pasta
directions: Defrost chopped spinach.
Cook pasta according to directions on the box.
Heat broth (or wine).
Add carrots, pepper, garlic and onion.
Saute until wilted slightly, then add mushrooms. Continue to saute until mushrooms are wilted.
Add defrosted spinach and simmer.
Add the Ricotta and mix well.
Remove from heat.
Fill each pasta and place into baking dish.
Once dish is filled, cover pasta with tomato gravy and sprinkle with cheese. Cover dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Add boned chicken and mix well.
Pour into large casserole pan, that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.
May be divided into two pans and one frozen for future use.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples and place in buttered 2-quart glass oblong baking dish.
Mix sugar and spices and sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle hot water over all.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour in a casserole dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or top is golden.

title: creole style lentils
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion in hot margarine in medium size saucepan until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar, pepper, pepper sauce and lentils.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
In a mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients and add flour mixture, mixing real well.
Drop by tablespoons on top of beef stew, chicken soup or sauerkraut, about 1/2 hour before serving.
Cover tightly and steam for 25 minutes.
Serve dumplings on or around the stew or whatever. Makes 5 servings.

title: butterscotch tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg, tea and vanilla.
Add oats, coconut and chopped nuts.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt; add to batter.
Chill for an hour or more. With lightly floured hands, shape into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Flatten with floured fork and place almond in center.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from baking sheet while warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar; add oil.
Combine flour and dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and zucchini; mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill 2/3 the way up. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a Teflon pan, melt the margarine and oil.
Add the marshmallows; heat until melted, being careful not to burn.
In a large pan, put the popcorn and pour the marshmallow mixture over it.
Mix well.
Let it set for a few minutes before adding the M&M's.
Toss well; press into a greased Bundt pan.
Remove after 1 hour.
Let it set for a couple of hours before slicing.
Use a sharp knife.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work all ingredients well with hands; form balls (about 1-inch in diameter).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wrap a piece of bacon around each chicken breast and secure with toothpick.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pineapple juice may be added. While chilling, mix one or two times.
May use large can of fruit cocktail in place of fruits.
Lite or no fat sour cream may be used.

title: eclair cake
directions: Spray or grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay one layer of graham crackers to cover bottom of pan.
Mix pudding and milk; add whipped topping.
Place half of pudding mix on cracker layer. Cover with another layer of crackers, rest of pudding and more crackers.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour until set.
Frost. Refrigerate overnight or 24 hours.
Cut through all layers and serve small (rich).

title: pie crusts (3) or 1 large cobbler
directions: Stir egg into warm water.
In the dry ingredients, blend shortening, then make a well in the center and pour egg/water into it.
Mix, then roll out for pie crusts.

title: green bean bake with onion
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Drain cooked beans.
Combine beans, soup, pimiento and lemon juice.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Continue baking, uncovered, about 5 minutes more or until onions are heated through.
Serves 6.

title: franks and green beans
directions: Preheat heavy skillet.
Add franks and brown on all sides. Cook celery and onion in broth until it has evaporated.
Add to the franks.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 2.
350 calories per serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add bread cubes.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple.
Mix all together, place in greased casserole with lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients. Melt the Crisco. Melt before measuring and pour over the dry ingredients; mix well. Lightly beat the eggs and vanilla. Mix with dough. Dough will be crumbly. Press into balls about the size of walnuts and bake on greased cookie sheet until lightly brown at 350°.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add sugar, oil, salt (if you use self-rising, omit salt) and egg.
Stir in 1 cup of flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth.
Place on oven rack over bowl of hot water; let rise 15 minutes.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Stir down batter and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir until mixed then turn onto floured board (cloth covered nice).
Knead 3 minutes.
If sticky, knead in 1/4 cup flour.
Divide dough into 16 pieces and shape quickly into balls.
Arrange in pan and brush tops with butter.
Cover with cloth and place on rack over bowl of hot water; let rise 25 minutes.
Heat oven to 425° and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from pan to wire rack. Brush tops with soft butter.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place about 2-inches apart on lightly greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serve warm
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: wild west casserole
directions: Crush chips slightly.
Place
half
on bottom of baking dish. Next layer	wieners.
Combine
other ingredients except cheese. Cover with remaining chips.
Sprinkle cheese, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruitcake
directions: Put first 3 items in 6-quart bowl.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves).
Take out 1/2 cup of this and add this to fruit to coat.

title: bean fondue dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of the cheese, until well blended.
Spread in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Wrap and refrigerate at this point if making ahead.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Serves 18.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix together taco seasoning and picante sauce.
Brown ground meat and onion; drain off any fat.
Mix in taco seasoning and picante sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Layer in large casserole dish as follows:
tortilla chips, seasoned ground meat, sour cream, diced tomatoes and finally, grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat in oven at 350° or microwave. Serve hot with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: mom's caramel coconut flan
directions: Place a 6-cup mold in a large shallow baking pan filled with 1-inch of hot water.
Place in a moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes to warm.
While mold is warming, heat 1 cup of the sugar in a small saucepan, stirring constantly, until melted and golden. Remove mold from water with pot holder.
Pour melted sugar into mold and swirl to coat bottom and sides with the caramel; cool slightly.
Beat eggs until foamy in a large bowl.
Beat in remaining sugar, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in coconut. Pour mixture into caramel-lined mold.
Replace mold in water bath. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
(Center will still be soft.) Remove from water bath.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Refrigerate until cold.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: *BLKLIN edges and the bony pieces in the center of the dish.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: In a large pan, combine sugar, water and coffee granules. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool and add vodka, brandy and vanilla.
Store in a glass container.

title: texas bake
directions: Cook hamburger and green pepper (drain); add taco seasoning and Italian sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cook rotini and drain; add sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture on top of that.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and syrup until mixture is light brown (about 8 to 10 minutes after boiling begins) on medium heat. Remove from heat.
Add soda and mix very well.
Pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and add all ingredients except cheese and Doritos. Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer in casserole dish (oblong). Start with Doritos, then meat, another layer of Doritos and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans.
Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to other mixture alternately with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Batter can be made ahead and stored in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: poppy sticks
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in oblong pan.
Roll dough in rectangle shapes and cut roll in 1/2-inch thick strips (long narrow strips). Roll in butter and cook in oblong pan at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle poppy seeds on top before baking.

title: pull-apart bacon bread
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes or until partially cooked. Drain on paper towels. Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Brush with 1 tablespoon oil. Cut into 1-inch pieces and place in a large bowl. Add the bacon, cheese, dressing mix and remaining oil. Toss to coat. Arrange pieces in a 5 x 9-inch oval on a greased baking sheet, layering as needed. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes or until doubled in size. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cover with foil and bake an additional 5-10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 1 loaf.

title: lasagne
directions: In Dutch oven or large skillet, cook and stir meats until brown.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes; break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Set aside 1 cup of meat sauce and 2/3 cup Mozzarella cheese.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart dish, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Stir well together.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes or until brown.
Be careful not to burn.
Stir in butter and vanilla; microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Very hot.
Add baking soda and stir gently, until light and foamy.
Work quickly, pouring onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: barbecue brisket roast
directions: Marinate brisket in first 6 ingredients, refrigerate overnight in pan sprayed with Pam.
Cover.
Take out, pour Worcestershire sauce over brisket.
Cover, cook for 3 hours.
Pour barbecue sauce and cook another hour at 275°.

title: seasoned carrots
directions: Clean carrots and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Bring to boil, add butter and seasonings.
Simmer for about an hour or until carrots are tender.
Increase heat to evaporate excess liquid (about 10 minutes) before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butter like grandma's
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature in a large bowl.
Add oil and buttermilk and beat on high speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Makes about 2 pounds.
To keep cholesterol low use corn oil and corn oil margarine.

title: sigma kappa sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, then other ingredients. Mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll dough in flour (about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick) and cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until just ready to brown (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
Frost when cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a cup, dissolve cornstarch in water.
In a bowl, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
In a pot, combine onion and butter.
Cook slowly until soft.
Add cornstarch, bouillon and milk.
Cook slowly, stirring often, until heated.
Add mace, salt and pepper.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
Combine salad dressing and remaining ingredients in a large skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring often, about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Pour over hot spaghetti, tossing gently.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: biscuit muffins
directions: With a pastry blender or knife, cut the margarine into the flour until particles are fine.
With a fork, gradually stir in the milk (mixture should be lumpy).
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onion and saute lightly in margarine.
Mash up squash with fork.
Combine onion and margarine mixture with slightly beaten eggs.
Add cream of chicken soup (undiluted) squash, corn bread, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Put Cheez Whiz in microwave to soften.
Pour over cooked rice and broccoli.
Add mushroom soup (3/4 can, no water) and onion. Place in buttered casserole dish and cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scallops meuniere
directions: Toss scallops in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in medium skillet.
Cook scallops 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spoon scallops over bed of rice.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over remainder of cake ingredients and stir well.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cointreau, Cool Whip and rind.
Mix well.
(Ideal for dipping or putting on fruit (pineapple, strawberries, bananas and melon.)

title: pat's vegetable dish
directions: Spray 9 x 12 pan with nonstick cooking oil.
Place veggies in layers; squash, celery, onions, carrots, green pepper, tomato; repeat process using all veggies.
Pour 2 c of partly cooked chicken bouillon broth over veggies.
Sprinkle garlic powder, cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350 F oven.
If adding cheese, remove foil, sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese browns.

title: easy salad
directions: Start by opening can of pineapple slices; drain all juice off. Put Jell-O in a 1 cup measure and add boiling water to make a cup. Stir until dissolved.
Pour in the can with pineapple slices. Place in refrigerator until set.
Next day cut the bottom from can. Push it through.
Slice with the slices.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with a scoop of cottage cheese.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Have 3 pounds of ground wild meat with absolutely no fat. Repeat:
NO FAT.
Mix ground meat with 3 tablespoons of "High Country Fish and Meat Jerky Seasoning" (original flavor).
Set overnight in refrigerator, covered.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Put in an ungreased dish and cover top with chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: wedding bell punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well.

title: sprite punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Stir in frozen limeade or lemonade. Add lime juice and extract. Serve. Pour into bowl over 1 1/2 quarts of cracked ice. Add Sprite. Makes 48 (4 ounce) servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is slightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into approximately 12 x 9-inch pan with cheese on top and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Spray pan with Pam for easy serving.

title: chicken-broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into small pieces.
Microwave broccoli packages 6 to 8 minutes or boil until cooked.
Place cooked broccoli in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer chicken on top.
In separate bowl, mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour into casserole. Cover with grated cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine over medium to low heat. Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Blend in dry gelatin.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
With buttered hands, form into balls. Makes 12 medium balls.
Recipe can be doubled and other flavors of gelatin can be used.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat oil in skillet.
Mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, egg and milk.
Pour oil into corn meal batter and stir.
Pour back into skillet.
Bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until sauce reaches desired consistency, stirring occasionally.

title: dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls
directions: Dinner Rolls:
Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl with boiling water until dissolved.
Add eggs, then water and yeast mixture, then flour.
If you need more flour to make dough medium consistency.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dinner rolls are made by greasing 2 dozen muffin tins.
Then roll into small balls with 2 or 3. Let rise with towel covering rolls for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until tops and bottom are brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add rice, onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until rice and ground beef are lightly browned.
Add 1 cup water, salt and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: the family's tuna salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna; boil, cool, peel and chop eggs.
Drain picklettes; combine mustard and mayonnaise.
Combine.
Chill and serve.
Enjoy!

title: amaretti-stuffed peaches
directions: Boil the wine and sugar for 5 minutes to form a syrup.
Poach the peach halves in the syrup for 5 more minutes, then lift out with a slotted spoon and let cool.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix ingredients and pour hot dressing over mixture.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: rich chocolate mousse
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in double boiler until they are of a smooth consistency.
Add the butter and stir into the hot, melted chocolate.
Stir in three tablespoons coffee and rum if desired. Separate the egg yolks from the whites.
Add the egg yolks to the chocolate mix, one at a time.
Beat the egg whites until the mixture is stiff and forms peaks.
Mix into the chocolate with a wooden spoon.
Pour the chocolate mousse into dessert glasses and leave to set in the refrigerator.
The chocolate mousse can be decorated with whipped cream and/or toasted almond slivers.
A sinfully rich dessert!

title: apple-carrot-raisin salad(with pineapple and nuts)
directions: Prepare fruit and vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Chill in fridge for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked halibut
directions: Marinate fillets in wine and salt for 4
hours.
Grease pan. Coat fish in 1 cup bread crumbs.
Put in oven dish.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup sour cream, and 1/2 cup onion.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 500° for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda and set aside.
Beat sugar, eggs and vegetable oil with mixer until smooth.
Slowly add flour mixture (using spoon instead of mixer) until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients to flour and sugar mixture.

title: cheese bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on water.
Add sugar, salt and 2 cups flour, then eggs and cheese.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Knead lightly.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered.
Divide into 2 loaves and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Keep in pans about 10 minutes before removing.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread pieces and allow to stand at room temperature until bread is moist.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir well.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased dish or pan.
Bake at 350° until brown or knife comes out clean when inserted in pudding.

title: plain layer cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to butter and sugar.
Beat whites; add the 1/3 cup of sugar and beat. Add cream as you blend in flour and egg whites.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken with gravy
directions: Pat chicken pieces dry with a paper towel; dip each piece first into seasoned flour, shaking to remove excess flour.
Then dip into the egg and back into the seasoned flour.
Quickly brown pieces in about 1/4-inch oil on medium-high heat.
After both sides of the chicken are browned, place on a broiler pan (to allow the juices to run through) in a preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
The chicken is done when juices run clear when chicken is pierced.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: De-head shrimp, but do not peel.
Place them in a shallow baking dish.
Make sauce by melting butter in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over shrimp.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, basting periodically.
Serve hot with warm French bread to dip in sauce.
Peel shrimp before eating.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 1/4 cup butter.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes, until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until bubbly.
Add sour cream.
Heat on low. Don't boil!
Serve over medium-wide egg noodles.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour and eggs together.
Pour milk over this and cook until thick.
Add butter, vanilla and half of coconut (if desired).
Pour into baked pie shells and put meringue on top.
Add remaining coconut on top.
Brown in 350° oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat slowly.
Pour over ham and return to oven for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Add mixture to the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Frost with peanut butter frosting given below.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook 4 chicken bouillon cubes, onion and celery in 1 quart water.
Cook and add the potatoes and mixed frozen vegetables for 30 minutes.
Add soup and cheese, cook until cheese melts.

title: stracciatella
directions: Add spinach to broth. Heat and cook in broth to defrost. Beat the eggs lightly in separate bowl. Add breadcrumbs, thyme and cheese and beat into egg. Makes a thick soup. Drizzle in egg mixture.
DO NOT STIR. Simmer three minutes. Separate egg gently with fork. Can also add some browned onion and maybe carrot.

title: makes its own crust custard pie
directions: Grease and
flour
a 9-inch glass pie pan.
Be sure all areas are
covered.
Combine
all
ingredients
in blender or processor for
30 seconds.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each chicken breast. Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Melt oleo.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll chicken in butter, then in crumbs. Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy biscuit lasagna
directions: Combine Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, parsley flakes and onions.
Mix well.
Separate a can of biscuits.
Press each to a 4-inch circle.
Place 2 tablespoons cheese mixture in each biscuit.
Fold over and seal edges.
Pour hot meat mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan and top with filled biscuits and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat mixture well.
Add milk, coconut and flavoring. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie is brown and firm.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix well with soup, tomatoes
and
chilies
and tapioca.
Line bottom of crock-pot with tortillas.
Add
of
the	chicken
and soup mixture. Sprinkle
with
onion and cheese.
Repeat layers of tortillas, chicken soup mixture, onion and cheese.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 hours.	Recipe may be doubled.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Heat olive oil and butter in skillet.
Add onion and next 3 ingredients.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in artichokes.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch quiche dish.
Top with mushrooms; sprinkle with Swiss cheese.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Fold tips of wings under to form a triangle.
Melt butter in large skillet; add wings and onion.
Cook for about 10 minutes or until wings are brown on both sides.

title: union pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 3 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: chinese chicken and noodles
directions: Dressing:
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
In food processor, process ginger, garlic and green onions until fine.
Whisk into soy mixture.

title: eunice ratliff's calico beans
directions: Fry
bacon
until
crisp.
Remove
bacon.
Crumble
and reserve.
Brown hamburger
in
bacon fat.
Add onion, ketchup, salt, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and bacon; simmer for five minutes.
Mix beans together and add to sauce.
Bake in baking dish or bean pot for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and cook in crock-pot slowly.

title: zippy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.
Refrigerate unused dip.

title: apple cake and icing
directions: Beat oil and eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat again.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir until blended. Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Add Cool Whip, pineapple, condensed milk and pecans.
Stir together until mixed.
Add lemon juice; stir.
Pour into crusts. Chill and refrigerate.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip into eggs; coat well with bread crumbs.
Cook in olive oil in skillet until tender and browned on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce into 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken in sauce.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheeses are melted and lightly browned.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chili verde(international cuisine)
directions: Brown pork, onion and bell pepper in large frying pan, making sure that pork is cooked well.
Drain fat from pan and sprinkle flour over mixture.
Dice Anaheim chilies and add with hot diced chilies into frying pan.
Let simmer for 45 minutes (or until thick).
Serve in small bowls.
Cut tortillas into small triangles and use tortillas as a scoop.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In large skillet, saute onion, garlic and pepper in oil until golden, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, tomatoes, parsley, oregano, bay leaf and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
In medium size bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, egg, 1/4 cup Romano, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Spoon 1/3 tomato sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of lasagna, half of the spinach and cheese filling, half of the Mozzarella and 1/4 cup Romano.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining sauce and Romano.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes about 1 hour but not thawed completely.
Mix everything except chips.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spray on top with Pam.
Bake at 350° until thickened, then put chips on top. Bake until chips are light brown, 1 to 1 1/2 hours total.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: priazzo
directions: Let bread dough rise.
Punch down and roll out for 9-inch pie pan, top and bottom crust.
Place bottom crust in pan.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Makes 3 medium pies or 2 large pies.
Mix ingredients except cinnamon.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Place butter in baking dish 9 x 13
x 2-inches.
Melt
in
oven.
In
large bowl combine eggs (beaten), flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese
and spinach.
Spoon into baking dish, level off.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, dry pudding and strawberries.
Stir well until all
is
blended.
Pour
into pie crust and garnish with coconut.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
It may need more flour. Should be a dough that will hold its shape when dropped from spoon onto oiled pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add vanilla.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press mixture on buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in order listed.
Blend well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Yields one 8-inch pie.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, celery and green pepper until fine. Blend remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Let stand overnight.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and next 6 ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Stir in rum and syrup. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons water if necessary to form mixture into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: praline pumpkin pie(make a day ahead)
directions: Prick pie shell and bake at 375° for 10 minutes until light brown.
In a skillet, cook butter, sugar and pecans, stirring until golden, about 3 minutes. Spread mixture onto sheet of foil. Cool and crumble. Sprinkle 1 cup over pie shell.
In saucepan, mix gelatin with cold water.
Cook over low heat until dissolved. Remove from heat and add brown sugar.
Blend in pumpkin, milk, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat cream until stiff but not dry. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into cooled pie shell and top with remaining praline pieces.
Beat 1/2 cup cream until stiff and gradually blend in vanilla and powdered sugar. Place a dollop of topping on each serving of pie.
Serves 8.

title: tutti-frutti pudding cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; reserve 1/2 cup liquid. Combine next 4 ingredients.
Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Add drained fruit cocktail and 1/2 cup reserved liquid.
Stir in flour mixture. Turn into an 8-inch greased and floured pan. Combine nuts and brown sugar.
Mix well and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream or other topping.

title: dilly bread
directions: Slightly warm together the cottage cheese and butter.
Add dill, onion, sugar, baking soda, salt and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Dissolve yeast in the warm water; stir into cottage cheese mixture.
Stir in as much flour as possible, then knead in the rest.
Continue kneading until dough is smooth.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease the top.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and chopped apples together.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add balance of ingredients to mixture. Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: After
cooking
bacon or sausage, leave grease in skillet. Add flour;
stir often to keep from burning.
Let brown. Then
add tomato
juice or diced tomatoes. Stir frequently to keep from being lumpy.
Add black pepper, if desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with celery and carrots in a big pot.
Remove celery and carrots.
Remove chicken from broth.
Add soup; season to taste.
Take meat off bone, put back in broth.
Tear tortillas into small pieces, add to broth at a full boil.
Cook for 15 minutes, without stirring, at a steady simmer.
Serve with vegetables.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan as follows:
pineapple, pie filling; then sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Put thin slices margarine or butter over entire cake. This may take 1 1/2 sticks.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream when served.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Melt cheeses in milk over low heat.
Stir in wine and crab. Serve in chafing dish with crackers.

title: german cheese balls
directions: Cream butter and
cream
cheese
in
mixer
bowl
until smooth; add sour cream and sugar.
Mix well.
Chill (1 hour or so); shape into balls.
Roll
in bread crumbs; place in bonbon cups to serve.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken linguini
directions: Put butter in a large skillet to melt.
Cook onion in melted butter until soft.
Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes.
Use the amount of milk listed in Alfredo Sauce directions and whisk milk and sauce mix into the soup.
Add the Alfredo Sauce mix and the milk mixture to chicken, stir well.
Add cheeses and simmer about half an hour.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mixture can be used on lettuce, slaw, red beets in a can. Measure beet juice and add water to equal 1 cup. Add cider vinegar and sugar. Bring mixture to a boil. Remove from heat. Pour over red beets and refrigerate overnight. Eat cold or heat.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add butter, beaten egg yolks and milk, then fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown and filling is set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Saute oil, onion and green pepper over medium heat.
Add sugar, vinegar and soup; bring to a boil.
Salt to taste.
Serve hot or cold (much better cold).

title: yogurt delight
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10 or 2 for a week.

title: almond chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed Rice Krispies, corn flakes or Special K cereal.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Coat first 4 ingredients with mayonnaise mixture.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and oleo.
Spoon into 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan.

title: pumpkin cookies (1)
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon & salt, set aside. Cream butter, gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate adding of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each.
Stir in chips.
Drop dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet.	Spread into pumpkin shape using thin spatula.
Add a bit more for stem.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cookies are firm & lightly browned.	Remove from sheets.

title: pinwheel hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix cream cheese and green chilies.

Open can of crescent rolls and lay flat in 2 long strips. Spread all of the cream cheese mixture evenly over both strips of dough. Roll each strip into a fat roll. Wrap each roll in waxed paper and refrigerate 1 hour or so.

title: amazing pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 buttered pie pans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown. Pie makes its own crust.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Mix pecans, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream together. Mix sugar, butter and milk together in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over pecan mixture and stir until smooth and blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to set until firm.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 120 pieces.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown. Let cool.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Melt butter.
Slowly add cream, salt and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add mushrooms and broccoli, pour over cooked noodles.
Serve hot.
Yields 7 (3/4-cup) servings.
Cooking time:
20 minutes at 300°.

title: corn beef dip no. 2
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Let chill before serving.
For best results, make the day before.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.
Serve in hollowed out bread, wheat crackers, chips.

title: meatballs
directions: Thaw ground turkey.
In a bowl, combine the turkey, egg, bread crumbs, lemon peel, parsley, fennel, peppers, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into large meatballs.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until crispy and brown.

title: beans in crock-pot
directions: Brown and drain meat and bacon.
Put in crock-pot for 5 hours or more.

title: baked french toast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices and place in pan.
Slightly beat eggs, sugar and vanilla. Stir in milk until well blended.
Pour over bread, turning slices to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy fruit cobbler
