directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit, like cake batter.
Pour into baking dish.
Spoon fruit on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until brown on top.
Good served with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add cheese, flour, salt, pepper, beaten eggs, sugar and butter to corn in a large	mixing bowl.
Slowly pour in heated milk, stirring often.
Pour
into
a
greased,
2 quart, round casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until firm.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown sugar.
Sift in powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Melt chocolate with shortening.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill 15 minutes, then cut into squares.
Continue to chill for at least 2 hours.

title: super nacho
directions: Heat beans through in saucepan.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning to ground beef.
Layer the heated beans in large round pan, then ground beef mixture, grated cheeses, lettuce and tomatoes.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Put sour cream in center.
Can add guacamole dip in center also.
Put Doritos chips around the outer edge.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Add raisins and fruit cocktail.
Blend well.
Then dice French bread and add to mixture. Let soak for about 10 minutes.
Pour into 10 x 6 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown in a 350° oven.
Delicious served with hard sauce.
Serves 6.

title: miss rose's meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Toss lightly to mix well. Shape mixture into meatballs. In Olive Oil, brown meatballs; remove and drain. Add to spaghetti sauce and simmer for about 1-1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet and sour chcken wings
directions: Mix all together in bowl, except chicken.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour over single layer of chicken wings.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: picnic slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot.
Add salt, sugar and celery seed; set aside.
In small saucepan, add vinegar, oil and mustard. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and stir.
Set in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch and 7-Up until thick.
While hot, mix with jello.
Put strawberries in pie crust.
Pour jello mixture over strawberries.
Put in refrigerator.
When cold, top with Cool Whip.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in double boiler.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice, butter, tapioca, salt and cinnamon in large frying pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, then reduce heat to simmer.
Add apples and cook for 10 to 15 minutes occasionally stirring gently until apples are tender.
Cool, cover and chill.

title: beef mandarin
directions: Saute beef, green pepper, scallions and garlic in oil.
Add water, soy and pepper sauces, liquid from mandarin oranges and salt and bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice, then oranges.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, each less than 350 calories.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain peaches.
Save the syrup.
Arrange peach slices in sugar mixture.
If desired, also arrange cherry halves, rounded side down, in sugar mixture.

title: christmas spice cake(2 layers)
directions: In large pot, mix ingredients.
Cook until it will form soft ball in cold water.
It will be caramel color when done.
Ice Christmas Cake with it.

title: cheese fondue (dip)
directions: Using a double boiler, rub inside with clove of garlic.
Heat wine; add Swiss cheese, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and well blended with wine.
Stir into cheese the instant potatoes mixed to a thin paste with water.
Cook for a few minutes to thicken.
Season with salt, red pepper and nutmeg.
Add Kirsch. Pour into silver chafing dish, being sure there is water under the dish.
If it thickens, add more Kirsch.
Serve with toasted bite-size pieces of French bread.
If bread cubes are used, provide "fondue forks" or "oyster forks."

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter and milk in a small saucepan until butter melts.
Do not boil.
Combine grated potatoes, peppers, onions and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour on milk.
Bake 4 hours, adding more milk if necessary.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Add salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Beat egg and milk.
Dip chops in liquid and roll in bread crumbs.
Put 3 tablespoons fat into skillet and brown chops.
Place chops in baking pan or dish. Add boiling water.
Cover and bake at 400° for about 50 minutes. Take the cover off last 10 minutes baking time.
These are very tender and delicious.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat water and egg white, then mix well with pecans.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, them mix with pecans.
Spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Step 1:
Grind veggies in food chopper.
Pour boiling water over veggies.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and let stand 2 to 3 hours.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Mix together good and pour over top of cake.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add salt and melted butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Add bananas, milk and soda; stir well.
Add flour and stir.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and well floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: canning beets
directions: Wash beets and
cook
until
done, but not soft.
Peel. Put mixture of sugar, vinegar, water and salt in a big pot and bring to boil.
Put
your
beets
in this mixture and let them get good and hot.
Put beets and peppers in jars and heat your mixture until it forms
a
rolling boil and pour over beets in jars. Screw tops on jars until tight.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn; put in a Pam sprayed brown paper bag, then set aside. Combine sugar, syrup and oleo in Pyrex measuring cup. Microwave on High 2 minutes; stir well. Cook 2 minutes on High; stir well. Add baking soda and vanilla; stir well.

Pour 1/3 of syrup over corn in bag. Stir with long handled, Pam-sprayed wooden spoon. Pour in another 1/3 syrup; stir well. Pour in remaining 1/3 syrup. Stir well. Fold down top of bag; place in oven. Microwave on High 1/2 minute; shake well. Repeat 2 times.

title: green chile salsa
directions: Chop jalapenos, tomato, onion and cilantro.
Mix together and add tomato sauce.
Add garlic and salt; continue mixing.
To thin, dilute with water slowly.
(For hotter, add more jalapenos.) Garnish with tortilla chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with crackers; pour margarine over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine the rice, 1 1/2 cups milk, sugar and salt.
Cook on medium heat or microwave on High until thick and creamy, stirring often (15 to 20 minutes).
Blend 1/2 cup milk with beaten egg. Stir into rice.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and raisins. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beth tartan's macaroni and lots of cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions; drain.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.

Set aside. Drain and rinse olives; set aside. Cut or tear the lettuce and place in a large bowl. Spread beans and olives on top of the lettuce. Spread grated cheese. Cut tomatoes into wedges and place on top of the cheese.
Just before serving, break up the tortilla chips and put on top of the tomatoes.
Pour dressing and mix.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place in a shallow casserole dish. Pour 1 tablespoon of sugar into the hole of each.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg and top each hole with 1 tablespoon of butter.

title: peanut butter banana pudding(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 25 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Spread about 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter between 2 vanilla wafers forming a sandwich; repeat procedure with remaining peanut butter and vanilla wafers.
Layer 1/3 of peanut butter and vanilla wafer sandwiches in bottom of 3-quart bowl; top with 1/3 of bananas.
Pour 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover and chill.
Spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with peanuts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken noodles 1800's style
directions: Dress a fresh, fat chicken and cook until tender.
Remove from broth and take from the bone.
In mixing bowl, break eggs.
Mix whites and yolks well.
Add salt.
Add flour until a stiff dough is formed.
Roll out very thin.
Cut in strips 3 inches wide. Stack and cut noodles into very thin strips.
Roll in flour to keep from sticking together.
Spread thin and let dry an hour or 2.
Drop into boiling broth and cook until tender.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Serve hot.

title: canning beets
directions: Wash beets.
Leave about 4 inches of stem.
Cook until tender. Drain.
Peel.
Peelings come off when run under cold water. (Wear plastic gloves to avoid staining hands.)
Cut into slices or wedges.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips. Blend cornstarch and soy sauce, then toss with chicken. Allow to set for 20 minutes. Over high heat in a large skillet, combine oil and garlic. Add chicken and cook several minutes. Add vegetables and cashews. Stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp. Combine water, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and cayenne pepper. Add to chicken mixture and cook until thickened. Serve with rice.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Place 2 cups rhubarb in pie shell and sprinkle 1/2 dry mixture over rhubarb.
Add eggs to other 1/2 of dry ingredients and beat well.
Add remaining 2 cups rhubarb to pie shell and pour egg mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add yogurt and marshmallow cream and stir.
Excellent for party fruit dip.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Cream white sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add soda water and vanilla and beat together.
Sift flour and salt and add to mix.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven until lightly brown and set.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: joanna's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shell.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm in the center.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind or grate zucchini and onion; sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again. Mix all other ingredients and pour over zucchini and onion.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: swissed beef steak in sour cream gravy
directions: Trim fat and bone from meat.
Cut into large square pieces; lay on plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Mix flour, mustard, salt, thyme and pepper.
Sprinkle all of it over meat on both sides. Cover with another sheet of plastic or waxed paper.
Pound meat until flour mixture is worked into meat and does not fall off when picked up.
Heat butter and oil in heavy casserole or Dutch oven. Brown meat on both sides.
Add remaining
ingredients, except sour cream.
Cover and simmer or bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir sour cream into gravy just before serving.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: beet pickles(beets are good pickled.)
directions: Mix ingredients, cook to boiling point, then pour over chunk pickles and cover them well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil until smooth, then add eggs one at a time. Add the flour, baking powder and salt that have been sifted together alternately with the sour cream. Add the vanilla. Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours. Bake on 2nd shelf from bottom.

title: pimento cheese baked grits
directions: Heat milk together with butter.
Blend in grits until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until grits are firm and lightly browned on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and serve on Bremner wafers or with fresh vegetables.

title: dip for fruit tray
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix good until thick.
Add Cool Whip; mix again and put on bottom of tray. Add fruit.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic, chili powder and onion to taste.
Combine all ingredients and Doritos just before serving.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Add milk if too thick.
Serve with corn chips.

title: red-raspberry nut muffins
directions: Combine egg, milk and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients. Stir into liquid mixture until moistened.
Quickly and gently, fold in raspberries and nuts. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: cabbage and noodle supreme
directions: Toast sesame seeds and almonds for about 10 minutes in 350° oven until brown. Place all ingredients in salad bowl and mix together.

title: low-fat sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut vegetables into large chunks.
Place with water in wok or large frying pan. Simmer until slightly crunchy. Combine cornstarch, vinegar, sugar, catsup and soy sauce.
Add to vegetables. Cook until thickened.
Add chicken nuggets and heat through.
Serve over cooked rice or Chinese noodles.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat
egg
whites
and salt until stiff.
Gradually add sugar to egg whites, beat 5 to 10 minutes with electric mixer. Stir
in vanilla and pecans, mix gently.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto
greased
cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour
or
until firm
to touch.
Store in airtight container. Makes 3 dozen.

title: fresh gooseberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 cup gooseberries.
Combine sugar, tapioca and salt. Add the whole gooseberries.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Pour into pastry-lined plate and dot with butter or margarine. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake about 30 minutes longer or until crust is done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in plastic bag with first 4 ingredients. Saute slowly in margarine.
Add last 3 ingredients and bake, uncovered, in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add hot water; cook over low heat until dissolved.
Add milk; cook until thickened.
Wonderful served over pancakes, homemade biscuits or ice cream.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Heat liquid of blueberries and pineapple and add enough water to make 4 cups of liquid in all.
Then dissolve jello in this hot mixture.
Let cool and add blueberries and pineapple and add chopped pecans and chill until firm.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the Thousand Island dressing, Knorr dry leek soup mix and the apricot preserves.
Place the chicken breasts in an oven dish; pour the mixture over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Baste one time during cooking.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Place boneless roast in a 325° oven for about 1 hour.
Pour all ingredients on top.
Cook for about 3 hours, or until roast shreds easily.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix well eggs, shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add vanilla, plain flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and apples.
Batter will be very thick.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add cream cheese to Jell-O mixture and stir until cream cheese is dissolved.
Measure drained juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add this with the marshmallows, pineapple and fruit cocktail to the Jell-O mixture.
Let congeal slightly and fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Makes a large bowl of salad.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Rinse kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Even better after 2 or 3 days.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: canned okra
directions: Place in a large cooking vessel and add enough water just to cover.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Place in sterilized jars.
Jars and lids need to be hot.
Seal.
Invert jars for 5 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In blender, combine sour cream, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and 1/4 cup Blue cheese.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining Blue cheese.
If necessary, stir in milk to make of desired consistency.
Cover and store in the refrigerator up to two weeks.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: butter pecan banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Do not underbake this cake.

title: 3-layer cake
directions: Mix flour and oleo until like cornmeal.
Add slivered almonds. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Mix sugar and cream cheese with 1 carton of the Cool Whip.
Put on top of the crust.
Mix pudding and milk; spread on top of cheese layer.
Spread last of the Cool Whip on top with almonds.

title: spiced cucumber rings
directions: Peel cucumbers and core out seeds.
Cut into rings, 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Dissolve pickling lime in water.
Add cucumbers and soak overnight.
Use granite or glass container.
Drain off lime water, wash and rinse in clear water several times.
Mix pickling vinegar, powdered alum and food coloring together.
Pour over cucumbers (use granite container) and add enough water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer until tender.
Drain and discard liquid.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll out and cut cookies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Beat powdered sugar, Crisco, salt, vanilla and milk together for frosting for cookies.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Remove from skillet.
Brown remaining flour mixture in oil until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Slowly stir in water.
Return chicken to skillet; add onion.
Cover and cook over low heat until done, about 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix by usual method using a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: french vanilla cake
directions: Combine
cake
mix, oleo and eggs.
Pour in greased pan. Mix cream
cheese,
eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix and spread on cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Chill juices and ginger ale. Pour all liquids in punch bowl. Add 1/2 gallon sherbet. Add remaining sherbet as needed.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar then add fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: "my favorite cheese ball"
directions: Mix together well, roll into a ball, then roll in crushed pecans.
Chill at least 8 hours, so flavors merge together.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: mundsack salad dressing
directions: Pour over shredded cabbage and refrigerate well before serving.
This is nice and crisp.

title: orange carrot congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cubes.
Cool until slightly set.
Cream together mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Stir in crushed pineapple and grated carrots.
Add mixture to slightly set Jell-O.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with coconut.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls. Bake for 10 min or until brown.

title: pineapple mimosa
directions: Measure 1 cup pineapple juice and 1 cup juice cubes or ice cubes into blender.
Whirl until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup champagne. Whirl 2 seconds.
Stand 30 seconds before pouring to allow foam to settle.
Pour into 2 or 3 glasses.
(To make larger quantity, fill blender to capacity using the given proportions.)
Makes about 15 beverages.
Pour pineapple juice in ice cubes trays and freeze for pineapple cubes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans and place in a 2 quart casserole dish. Combine soup, seasonings and sour cream; add to beans along with 1/2 of the onion rings and almonds.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated flank
directions: Place flank in flat pan; pour soy, water, little olive oil and a dash of Worcestershire sauce below top of meat.

Spread fresh rosemary and thyme on top of meat. Sprinkle salt (may be omitted) and pepper. Marinate for 2 to 3 days in refrigerator; turn over daily. Bake as is at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes as desired. Do not overbake. (Do not cover during baking.)

title: pot likker dumplings
directions: Have a large pot of turnip greens, cooked with ham hocks simmering.

title: grandma's santa claus cookies
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and brown sugar.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture. Mix together eggs and nuts and add to flour mixture.
Line one or more loaf pans with wax paper and flatten dough into loaf pans, making sure to tap down well.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Just before baking, slice thin and place on greased cookie sheet. Return to refrigerator to keep cool until ready to use.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put chicken in buttered casserole dish. Layer cheese on top. Mix soup, wine, salt and pepper; pour over cheese. Sprinkle mix on top and drizzle with melted butter. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini angelino
directions: Mix.
Spread in greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Add flour and baking powder mixture to egg and milk mixture.
Add cherries to batter. (Batter is stiff enough if cherries don't sink to the bottom.)
Pour into buttered casserole dishes (one large and one small).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness with cake tester.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: noodle kugel (pudding)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water as directed on package.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks with sour cream, cottage cheese, sugar, vanilla and pepper.
Fold in noodles.
Fold in egg whites.
Add apples, sliced and rolled in sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, uncovered.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, broccoli and soup; then add half of grated cheese. Pour into pan.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttercup cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, and salt. Add shortening, buttermilk, vanilla, and other flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Add 2 eggs.
Beat 2 minutes on high.
Pour into 2 greased round 8 inch pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mid east salad
directions: Toss green pepper, tomatoes, cucumber and green onions. Combine yogurt, dill, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over salad and toss.
Also good on pita bread.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yield 1 1/2 cups.
Carbohydrate 1 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories per serving 4. One third tablespoon = free food exchange.

title: party cheese melts
directions: Mix together and spread on individual party rye slices.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: peanut butter cups(lighter eating - 2 points)
directions: Mix cool whip and peanut butter. Put into cupcake liners. Drizzle top with syrup and freeze.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat and melt grape jelly.
Add mustard to taste.
Add wieners. Cook in crock-pot, low setting for at least 3 hours; stirring occasionally.

title: pierogi pie
directions: Cook potatoes and mash with cheese.
Cook noodles.
Saute onions in butter.
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch).
Layer noodles, potatoes, onions and butter mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cornish with apricot glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare rice according to package directions. Rinse hens in cool water & pat dry. Stuff hens loosely with cooked rice. Fold wings back & tie legs together. Season outside of hens with tarragon, salt & pepper. Place in large shallow baking pan, breast side up. Bake, basting frequently with glaze, 1 hour & 10 minutes or until internal juices of hen run clear. (Or insert instant - read meat thermometer in thickest part of hen. Temperature should read 180 degrees.)

title: walnut noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a bowl, mix walnuts with sugar.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add walnut mixture, stirring often until slightly glazed.
Add noodles.
Mix well and serve warm.

title: peach preserve cake
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, cloves, cinnamon and salt. Cream together margarine and sugar.
Then add eggs, one at a time. Put soda into buttermilk and beat into egg mixture.
Add flour mixture and preserves.
Mix well, then add pecans.
Bake in tube or large loaf pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.
This cake can be frozen for weeks.

title: louisiana pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Remove from oven, leave in pan and cover tightly with dry towel until cold, for at least one hour.

title: rice and chickpeas(garbanzos)
directions: To boiling water, add all ingredients except parsley.
Cook over medium heat, uncovered.
When rice has absorbed most of the water, turn heat to low.
Cover and continue cooking until all the water is absorbed.
Garnish with parsley and serve with yogurt and cucumber salad.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces several hours or overnight.
Place on cookie sheet or shallow pan.
Do not cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for about a hour.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients well and store in a tightly covered jar.
Each serving, 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli in cold water; break off flowerets.
Mix dressing.
Will be thick when first mixed.
Gets thinner as it gets cold.
Refrigerate; stir often.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, layer graham crackers.
Prepare pudding. Layer 1/3 pudding over crackers.
Repeat layers 2 more times. Chill.
Cover top with Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and Bisquick until crumbly.
Add sausage (at room temperature) and mix thoroughly.
Roll into bite size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Crumble cake mix and butter together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream frosting and cream cheese together.
Pour on cake from the center to the edge.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: jordyn's gram's fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes; stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano. Combine 2 beaten eggs and the Mozzarella cheese.
Stir in the zucchini mix.
Separate crescent rolls; arrange in 8 x 12-inch baking dish, pinching perforations and pushing up sides of dish. Spread crust with mustard and turn in zucchini mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: carrots, israeli style
directions: Peel or scrape carrots and cut into 1/4-inch slices. (Diagonal slices are more attractive than round.
If you have a corrugated cutter, use it to slice the carrots.) Put in saucepan with butter, wine and nutmeg.
Cover and cook over low heat until carrots are tender.
Stir in raisins and sugar and continue cooking a few minutes longer, until raisins are plump and carrots are glazed.
This is different and extraordinarily good.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all but 1/2 of the cheese.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Put in layers in a large pan: 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of cake (crumbled), 1/2 of fruit cocktail and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Then repeat.
Then garnish with maraschino cherries on top.

title: buttermilk chess cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes one pie (use small pie shell).

title: chocolate cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift and mix flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 325° and bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before turning.

title: mock crab dip
directions: Chop up crab meat.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add onions, crab and seasoning.
Serve with Wheat Thins or use as a salad accent.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients; pour in ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake the cake according to directions.
When cake comes out of oven, pierce it all over with a fork.
Pour caramel topping and condensed milk over hot cake.
Let cake cool.
Ice with Cool Whip and garnish with crushed Heath bars.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan or dish.
Mix corn meal, eggs, onion and cheese.
Add the cooked broccoli.
Pour this in pan or dish over the melted butter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken and remove from bones.
Place the chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Slice the eggs and place on top of the chicken.
Put the peas and carrots over the chicken.

title: an evening of poetry
directions: In a blender, mix water, juices and bananas for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add apple and strawberries; mix for 1 more minute. Makes 5 cups.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Mix water, soda and vanilla; add to the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Bake at 370° for 35 minutes.
Pour powdered sugar icing over cake when done.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions. Meanwhile, melt the butter over medium-low heat and stir in the cream, pepper and garlic powder. Cook for 6 to 8 minutes, or until hot, stirring constantly. Stir in the parmesan cheese until thoroughly combined. Cook for 3-5 minutes, or until thickened. Toss pasta with sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape meat mixture into loaf.
Add vegetables.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: corn and zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini; cook, covered, in small amount of salt water until tender.
Drain and mash with fork.
Cook onion in butter. Combine eggs, zucchini, onion, corn, cheese, and salt.
Pour into casserole.
Mix butter, bread crumbs, and cheese (Parmesan). Sprinkle on top.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 300° until brown and bubbly.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.

title: brown butter balls
directions: Mix nutmeg and sugar.
Mix dates and peanut butter.
Combine the two mixtures; add the lemon juice.
Form into small balls. Makes about 30.

title: sweet yams
directions: Quarter yams and cook until fork goes in gently; do not overcook.
Drain.
Make a mixture of butter or margarine and sugar.
Roll potatoes in mixture.
Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 375° until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sunday french toast
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in large baking pan.
Beat eggs, milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt well.
Pour over bread, turning slices to coat evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Refrigerate!
Heats well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the carrots and nuts to the egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour the batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake is done.

title: eggplant patties
directions: In covered saucepan, cook eggplant in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain well and mash.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, onion, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Cook in hot oil for 5 minutes on each side.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add all, except soda.
Cook until peanuts are done over medium heat.
Add soda and spread fast on a buttered cookie sheet.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over ice cubes or chipped ice.

title: zucchini relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine zucchini and onions.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
The next day, put 6 (1-pint) or 12 (1/2-pint) canning jars with rings and lids into a large pot of water.
Bring to a simmer.
Drain zucchini and onions.
Rinse in cold water; drain.

title: chicken in crock-pot
directions: Put cut up fryer in crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper and sprinkle with paprika.
Add soup and mushrooms.
Cook on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or cook on slow for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: dilly beans
directions: After beans have been thoroughly cleaned, pack into jars lengthwise, leaving 1-inch headspace to each pint. Add 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 dill head. Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boiling point. Pour over beans while boiling hot and seal. Process for 10 minutes in hot bath. Let beans sit for 2 to 4 weeks to allow flavor to develop. Makes 4 pints.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs,
gradually
add milk while beating.
Last add hot water, slowly,
still using mixer to mix.
Bake crust a few minutes to prevent
sogging.
Add all of mixture and bake until custard consistency.

title: mississippi dirt pudding
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc., and check that rum again for quality!
It must be just right.
Try again.
With an electric beater, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and beat again. Meanwhile, make certain that the rum is of best quality.
Add 2 large eggs and 2 cups of baking powder.
Add a pinch of rum, 1 teaspoon soda and 1 cup of pepper or maybe salt.
Anyway, don't fret.
Just test that rum again.
Zowie!!
Next, sift in half a pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped buttermilk and add strained nuts.
Sample rum again.
Add 1 bablespoon srown tugar or whatever color is around!
Mix well.
Grease oven and turn on cake pan to 350°.
Now pour the whole mixture into the oven and---oops!
On second thought and also third and fourth, forget the cake.
Check the rest of the rum and go to bed.
Merry Christmas and Happy New Year!!!

title: elderberry wine
directions: Cook berries and water only a few minutes, just long enough to scald thoroughly.
Let strain through cheesecloth.
Add 8 cups sugar to 10 cups berry juice.
Set in cool place; skim daily until clear.
When bubbles cease to rise on top of liquid, it is ready to bottle.

title: ham casserole
directions: Melt margarine; cook onion, pepper, flour, milk and soup together in melted margarine.
Put chopped ham in casserole (9 x 13-inch); sprinkle with lemon juice.
Pour cooked mixture over ham.
Split biscuits in half (stretch as much as possible without tearing up); place on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. When it becomes bubbly, sprinkle with a cup of grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: teriyaki beef bits
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Combine sherry, honey, soy sauce and lemon juice in deep bowl.
Add meat and stir to coat well. Marinate for 30 minutes.
Spread meat pieces apart in baking pan. Bake at 475° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Great served with steamed rice.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix together until well blended.
May use for sandwiches or as a spread for crackers.

title: hot crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on English muffin halves. Cut into quarters. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Yields 48 triangles.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients. Spoon onto waxed paper by teaspoons.
Let set.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in crock-pot and cook on low for 3 hours.

title: fresh apple nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to margarine mixture and then stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bite-size corn dogs
directions: Cut each hot dog into 3 pieces.
Dip each one into batter. Drop into hot oil.

title: stir-fried bok choy
directions: Spray a wok or large skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Preheat over medium-high heat.
Add the sliced bok choy, sweet pepper strips and garlic.
Stir-fry the vegetables for 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, sugar and sesame oil; toss to coat.
Transfer the stir-fried vegetables to a platter or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed. Makes 2 or 3 side dish servings.

title: apple dip(perfect for kids!)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients until brown sugar has blended into cream cheese and vanilla. If mixture is too thin, add brown sugar. If mixture is too thick, add vanilla. You can add peanut butter, nuts or use flavored cream cheese. Serve with apple slices.

title: susan justice mother's brownies
directions: Blend boiling water and cocoa and let cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each.
Beat in flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in cocoa mixture and nuts.
Beat well.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, syrup and oleo in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium to low heat; stir constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in salt and milk.
Serve over ice cream or cake or pudding.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Divide batter in half; add chocolate to one half and mix.

title: double decker brownies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs and beat. Add alternately with dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Place 1/3 of batter in small bowl.
Add chocolate and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange graham crackers over batter in pan.
Add chocolate bits to remaining batter.
Drop by spoonfuls over crackers and spread to cover.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Cut into squares or bars while warm.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in tarts and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then 350° for a few minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in a glass casserole.
Blend juice, teriyaki sauce, vinegar and catsup.
Add meat and green peppers, and mix well.
Microwave, covered on high for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks.
Microwave covered 12 to 15 minutes on medium.

title: m&m peanut butter bars
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and mix thoroughly.
Add Special K and add M&M's. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in the olive oil until tender. Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, until well blended.

title: bacon wrap
directions: You will need 30 toothpicks for this recipe.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix together and shape into patties; brown.
Mix together 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over patties.
Cover and cook on low for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: seven layer salad(weight watchers)
directions: Layer ingredients, except yogurt and sweetener, in a salad bowl.
Start with lettuce and end with bacon bits.
Mix yogurt and sweetener.
Pour over salad.
Refrigerate.
Serves 1.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into
jelly
roll pan and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, salt and sugar.
Stir in cornmeal.
Combine eggs, vinegar, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until they are just moistened.
Turn into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Heat
all ingredients and remove spices before serving. Keep hot.
This
is
nice
to serve during the Christmas holidays.

title: polywogs
directions: Melt caramels and add ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool.
Dip in chocolate; let cool.

title: raw cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion, milk, salt and pepper until smooth. Break cauliflower into small pieces and add with celery and peas in mayonnaise mixture.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in kettle.
Cover and heat.
Makes 10 to 12 cups.

title: creamy-crunch green beans
directions: Drain beans, saving 1/4 cup liquid.
Mix liquid with soup, heat until smooth.
In casserole dish, gently fold soup mix into beans.
Top with onion rings.
Heat, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Combine ingredients; cook.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: olde english trifle
directions: Spread the sponge cake with jam.
Cut up in small pieces. Place in large bowl.
Place macaroons on top.
Pour thickened custard all over.
Spread whipped cream over top.
Sprinkle sliced almonds on top.
Decorate with cherries so it resembles the queen's crown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dough will be sticky.
Roll out.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are a soft, almost cake like cookies.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, sugar, salt and milk really good. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise, buttermilk, celery seed and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Stays fresh and crispy for several days.

title: three cheese dip
directions: In a small bowl, with an electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually blend in milk.
Add remaining cheeses; beat until well blended.
Serve as a dip with crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together; heat well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix and cook for 3 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry muffins(microwave)
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add blueberries. Add milk, melted butter and egg.
Mix until dry ingredients are just moistened. Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into paper lined microwave-safe baking or cupcake pan. Don't fill more than 2/3 full.
Microwave on Medium-high power for 3 minutes. Let rest for 3 minutes.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes or until muffins are done.
They will be a little soft in the center.
Let them rest in the pan a couple of minutes before serving.

title: company potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes as desired.
Add the other ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Dot with butter, paprika and parsley flakes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the sugars and flour.
Add the butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: dandelion salad with bacon dressing
directions: Toss together chopped dandelion, chopped onion and fried bacon pieces.
Set aside.
In skillet, warm butter and cream until butter melts.
Beat egg and then add salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and flour.
Blend the egg mixture into the slightly warm cream mixture.
Increase heat and cook, stirring constantly until the mixture thickens.
Pour hot dressing over the greens and toss gently.
Serve at once.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water, corn syrup, maple syrup and salt and boil mixture to 238° (thread).
Add peanuts and boil to about 295°. Stir frequently, as this will burn easily.
Then add butter and soda, mixing well. Pour in 2 buttered sheet pans, shaking it thin. When cool enough, break into pieces.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and cream of tartar and set aside.
Cream butter, oil, sugar and confectioners sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy using an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Gradually stir in the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add walnuts. Drop by rounded teaspoon/tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each with the bottom of a greased drinking glass dipped only once in oil, covered with sugar. Decorate.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
Remove and cool on a rack.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil, skin and mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shells.
(Makes 2 pies.) Cook approximately 35 minutes in oven at 350°.
You may add 1 cup of coconut if desired.

title: peach or apricot salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil and boil 2 minutes; cool until it begins to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip, which has been blended with the buttermilk.
Congeal.
Serves 12.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Open first three cans of beans; drain and set aside.
Saute 3 large onions (chopped) in bacon grease, then drain.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Stir in soups and add crawfish tails.
Stir in rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Heat in 350° oven until hot.

title: old fashioned muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into cups, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve warm.
Very good and easy recipe.

title: fruit blox
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over cold juice and let stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice and stir until dissolved.
Stir in honey and pour into 8-inch pan.
Chill.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter, then add sugar, flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add coconut. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown together ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves 16.
Each serving has only 6 gm fat and 153 calories.

title: marian's beef barbecue(sloppy jo)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until onion is clear in color.	Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: holiday punch
directions: Let sherbet soften in refrigerator.
In large container, mix lemonade and orange juice with water according to directions.
Add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving. Works best if pineapple juice and ginger ale are cold.
May add red food coloring for holiday.

title: apple pie
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt, oil and milk to make crust for 9-inch pie.
Roll half of dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Place in pie plate.
Roll second half and place on top of completed pie.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix dry ingredients. Toss over apples.
Mound in pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until soft but not brown.
Roll out crackers and put in skillet with melted margarine.
Layer buttered crumbs, onions and grated cheese in casserole, ending with crumbs on top.
Sprinkle canned milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add vanilla and peanut butter; cool 5 minutes.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
You can use nuts or crunchy peanut butter.

title: noreen's summer squash
directions: Place all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Marinate overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and mix into flour mixture.
Put in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Frost.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Heat oil in large stock pot.
Saute celery, pepper, onion and garlic.
Add broth, tomatoes, okra, thyme, bay leaf and red pepper.
Salt to taste. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add catfish and simmer 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with potato chips and the grated cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chicken fingers with a kick
directions: Cut chicken into 2 or 3 inch slices and dip into milk beaten with egg. The dip into flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Brown in hot oil in a large frying pan. Melt butter a large baking dish, stir in the hot sauce, place browned chicken fingers in the dish, cover with aluminum foil, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole 1
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Brown onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except for noodles and cheese.
Simmer until nice consistency.
Cook noodles. Drain and mix with meat sauce.
Put half of sauce in bottom of 3-quart dish.
Cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot bricks
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepot; add butter, sugar and nutmegs.
Add booze and bring back up to hot, but do not boil (that would boil booze out).
Serve in warm mugs.
Makes 25 servings.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Rinse chicken,
pat dry with paper towels.
Remove any excess fat from inside chicken.
Starting at the neck opening, use your fingers to loosen skin from the meat to create a pocket on each side of breast.
Leave skin attached to the breast bones.
Rub the garlic onto the meat underneath the skin.
Place the rosemary under the skin.
Place the chicken, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Loosely stuff with some of the potatoes, carrots, onions and fennel.
Place remaining vegetables in pan around chicken.
Skewer the neck skin to the back of chicken and tie legs to tail.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of thigh.
Pour water into bottom of pan.
Roast, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn vegetables over and roast, uncovered, 30 minutes or until thermometer registers 180° to 185° and chicken is no longer pink.
Transfer vegetables to serving dish and keep warm.
Loosely cover the chicken with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.
Serve the chicken with vegetables.
Remove and discard skin before eating.

title: caramel icing
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar and cream.
Cook several minutes with lid on.
Remove lid and bring to a boil. Allow to boil several minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add butter; remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy; spread on cake.
Very good on angel food cake.

title: pickle roll-up
directions: Drain pickles; spread each slice of ham with cream cheese. Put a pickle at narrow end of ham slice and roll up, jelly roll style.
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy ham sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the ham, process cheese spread, mayonnaise and onion.
Place 1/3 cup of mixture on bottom of each bun.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and process cheese spread begins to melt.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix well.
Great for kids to do on their own !!!!!

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add a large box strawberry jello.
Arrange strawberries in pie shells and pour hot mixture over.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.
Yields 2 pies.

title: sweet mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar.
Let stand overnight.
Beat in eggs, sugar and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add mayonnaise.

title: crescent delight
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan candy
directions: Melt sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add morsels, pecans and marshmallow cream.
Stir until mixed good.
Pour into large cookie sheet. Makes about 4 or 5 pounds.
Very good candy.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and black pepper to taste.
Dredge the rump roast in the flour and cover evenly.
Shake off excess.
In a large pot over medium-high heat, melt the butter and brown the roast on all sides.
Place in a 4 quart casserole dish with lid.
In a small bowl, combine the soup mix, mushroom soup, and vermouth or white wine; pour over roast.
Cover and bake in preheated oven for 3 hours or until desired doneness.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix in wheat germ, then add remaining ingredients. Beat until well blended.
Oil an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and pour in. Bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes - crock-pot style
directions: Pare and thinly slice potatoes.
Toss slices in water and cream of tartar.
Drain.
Put half of sliced potatoes in greased crock-pot.
Top with half of onion slices, flour, salt and pepper. Add remaining sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with remaining flour.
Add butter and undiluted soup.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Add cheese slices a few minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients (except pie shell) to egg mixture and combine well.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: taco dip(easy and delicious)
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Top and spread with chili.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese has melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crusty oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Add parsley, if desired.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip chicken in butter and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Soak the meat in salted water for several hours.
Simmer slowly for 2 hours, skimming occasionally.
Let the broth stand overnight.

title: swans made easy
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add the flour all at once.
Stir constantly with a wooden spoon until the mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Dough is ready to shape.
Fun for children to do.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together and add to mix.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows evenly over cake.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: jigglers gelatin snacks
directions: Stir boiling water or apple juice in large bowl, stirring 3 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Pour into 13 X 9 pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water for about 15 seconds.
Cut into decorative shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin.
Lift from pan.
Makes about 24 pieces or 4 to 6 servings.

title: speedy doughnuts
directions: Separate biscuits into 20 biscuits.
Cut hole in center of each biscuit.
Fry in hot oil at 375° for about 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and sugar.
Serve warm.

title: amazing corn cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn and sugars.
Add eggs and oil; beat until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients; add to batter and mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool thoroughly.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add baking powder, soda and flour, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by ice cream scoop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350° until slightly browned.
For smaller cookies, drop by rounded tablespoonfuls and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt eva's chocolate pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour, salt and cocoa together.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, bring milk almost to a boil.
Add dry mixture and stir until it begins to thicken.
Add butter and egg yolks; stir until thick enough for pie.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cool.
Add meringue and bake.

title: quick and easy chili dip
directions: Stir together and heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with dip size tortilla chips.

title: salmon creole
directions: Remove bone and skin from salmon and flake.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Add bread crumbs and stir to coat.
Add half of crumbs to mixture and combine.
Turn into 9 x 9-inch greased casserole pan. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased iron skillet at 425° until done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until smooth.
Butter a large pie plate; dust with crushed chocolate wafer crumbs.
Pour mixture in and bake for 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool slightly.
Mix sugar (about 3 tablespoons), sour cream and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla together.
Pour on top and bake another 20 minutes.
Cooking time is 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and brown.
Add 2 cans of pork and beans; simmer.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on low heat, stirring continuously until boils.
Cool.
Serve with sliced apples or as a topping.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Rinse peas well; place in large pot and cover with water by 1-inch; soak overnight. Drain peas and add 7 cups fresh water along with all ingredients listed above. Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 1 to 2 hours or until beans are tender. Stir occasionally, mashing beans and potatoes against sides of pot to thicken soup. Makes about 10 bowls.

title: forever slaw
directions: Shred or chop cabbage.	Slice onion and pepper thin.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt. Pour over cabbage.	Cover and let this sit for 6 hours.
Mix. Keep forever in refrigerator.

title: date pudding
directions: Make a thin syrup of brown sugar and the water.
Pour into a rectangular baking dish and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Mix the dates and nuts with the flour and baking powder to keep them from settling to the bottom of the pudding.
Add to the sugar, butter and milk mixture. Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls into syrup.
Bake about 1 hour in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, adding a small amount and beating.
This is important.
Add flavoring, beat until creamy.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour; increase heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Do not preheat oven.

title: mustard salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat with mixer until blended and thick.
Store in a tight jar in refrigerator.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thick.
Mix in 1 cup whipped topping.
Stir in 3/4 cup strawberries; pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Whisk pudding into milk; fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Stir in strawberries; spread mixture over pie crust and gelatin.
Chill until set, 2 hours.
Garnish with additional strawberries.

title: carrot soup
directions: Brown hamburger and set aside.
In same pan, cook celery, onion and bell peppers about 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients plus hamburger and cook over low to medium heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with small cubes of Swiss cheese on top.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in square 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and egg until well blended.
Pour in pan over melted margarine.
Do not mix.
Then spoon fruit or pie filling over batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serve warm or cold.
May top with vanilla ice cream.
Recipe can be doubled for a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: spiced baked apples
directions: Combine the raisins and nuts; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring brown sugar, water, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Core apples and place in an ungreased 2-quart baking dish; fill with raisin mixture.
Pour sugar mixture over and around apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Yield: 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.

title: scripture fruit cake
directions: Slice almonds, citron and figs.
In mixing bowl, follow Solomon's advice for making good boys (Proverbs 23:14).

title: apple-blueberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Beat together butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in applesauce, then dry ingredients only until blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove to wire rack to cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
(Any fruit may be used instead of blueberries.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat thoroughly. Good served hot or cold.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water; set aside.
Chop vegetables.

title: salted pecans
directions: Melt margarine in large baking pan; add pecans and salt.
Stir well to coat pecans.
Remove from heat.
Place pecans in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Blend sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients together separately.
Add all together.
Cool dough in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Roll in small balls; dip top in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put corn bread twist into a 9 x 13 pan.
Flatten and seal together.
Crush 1/2 bag tortillas and sprinkle over corn bread crust.
Layer taco meat, salsa, sour cream, onions and green peppers.
Sprinkle remaining crushed tortilla chips and top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Add Meringue Topping and brown.

title: broccoli 'n' cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, set aside. Combine oil and next 5 ingredients; stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently to coat; cover and chill 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon over lettuce, if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: s'more
directions: Place 4 sections of chocolate on 1 graham cracker.
Poke pointed green sticks through 1 large marshmallow.
Toast over the hot coals until marshmallow is brown, then slip it onto the chocolate and top with remaining graham cracker.
Eat like a sandwich.
Want s'more?

title: irish fruit loaf
directions: Steep currants, raisins and sugar in a cup of warm tea overnight.
Next day, stir in egg, marmalade, allspice and flour. In a greased or lined baking tin, pour in mixture and top with a few knobs of butter and a sprinkle of sugar.
Bake for 1 3/4 hours at 350°.

title: apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots.
Cover with water; boil for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Chop cooled apricots.
Mix into crumbs with a pastry blender the butter, sugar and 1 cup flour.
Press crumbs into a square 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
With a whisk, beat eggs lightly.
Add brown sugar, 1/3 cup flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add chopped apricots. Spread apricot mixture over just out of the oven hot baked layer; bake another 30 minutes.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, chips, nuts and cherries (any combination works great).
Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add orange juice and mix well.
Slowly add flour mixture, about 1/3 at a time.

title: kielbasa skillet stew
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove to paper towel to drain.
In drippings, cook onion and sausage until the onion is tender; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend in all milk and eggs.
Turn into unbaked pie shells and bake in 400° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.

title: mexican dish dinner
directions: Brown beef; add beans, chili and tomatoes.
Cook until it starts to simmer.
Add cheese and whipping cream (do not whip cream).
Heat again until cheese melts and starts to simmer. Serve over Fritos with salad and hot bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine all ingredients and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Top with enough additional bread crumbs to cover ingredients and dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain off grease.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Add beans (drained) to this sauce mixture. Combine hamburger mixture to sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Or can be put in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and place in loaf pan.
Baste top with following sauce.

title: raspberry chipotle wraps
directions: In a large bowl, combine spring greens, chicken breasts, raspberry chipotle ranch dip, avocados and cheese.
Place 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll into a cone.
Secure each wrap with a sheet of foil or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lipton onion soup roast
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish or roasting pan. Place pot roast in mixture.
Cover tightly and bake for 2 1/2 hours or until tender in 350° oven.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in the blender.

title: low-fat teriyaki potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut new potatoes into quarters or the medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place the potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Add the margarine, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning and black and red pepper; toss to combine.
Cover and cook on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender, stirring twice during the cooking.
Stir again before serving.
Garnish with the rosemary, if desired.
May be served as is or with nonfat sour cream.
Serves 5.
Contains 155 calories and 2 grams fat per serving.

title: breast of chicken with orange sauce
directions: Place onion, carrot and orange rind in bottom of shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Mix 1/2 cup orange juice and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same pan chicken cooked in, combine stock, remaining orange juice, ginger, cornstarch and juices in pan.
Heat until sauce thickens, stirring often.
Pour over chicken.
Garnish.
Serves 4.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Peel and
grate potatoes into bowl; mix in butter, sour cream, onions,
salt
and	pepper.
Place	in
a
buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top
with cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie no. 1
directions: Combine powdered sugar, peanut butter and peanuts until consistency of
biscuit
mix.
Spread
of this mixture on baked
crust bottom.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk and mix
well.
Add
gradually
to
beaten
egg yolks and cook until thickened.
Add
butter
and vanilla and carefully pour custard over
mixture in baked crust.
Top with meringue, made with 3
egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle meringue with balance of
peanut butter mixture and bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Split squash and steam until done, let cool. Take a fork and shred out the filling of the squash into a baking dish. Add the sauce, meat and onion. Season, mix well and cover with cheese. Bake in oven at 350 degrees until hot through and cheese is browning slightly.

title: cream cheese and bacon dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites and salt together.
Gradually add sugar.
Fold in crumbs, then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Top with 1/2 cup whipped cream.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 14 x 10-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done and lightly brown on top.
Let cool.
Cut into desired size for serving.

title: deviled steak
directions: Pound flour, salt, pepper and Accent into steak.
Cut into strips about 2-inch size.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Add chopped onion before meat is done.
Mix catsup, stock, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Pour over meat, stirring to dissolve. Cover tightly and simmer at 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Lay pepper strips on top for 20 minutes.
Add water as needed.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in a skillet.
Add soup, water, seasonings and corn.
Mix well and allow to simmer for 15 minutes. Fill a greased pie dish or casserole dish 3/4 full, leaving room for Cornbread Top.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except biscuits and cheese. (Brown hamburger and drain.)
Bring to a boil.
Put in casserole dish.
Add Hungry Jack biscuits on top of casserole and put on grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° .

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend dry ingredients and cereal.
Add liquid until moist. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes enough muffins for later use. Will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: cheese spread on rye
directions: Mix and spread on slices of party rye bread.
Heat in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter, oil, cocoa and water; bring to a boil. Combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon in a bowl; pour butter mixture over. Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: crispy easter nests
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Add noodles and plain chocolate candies.
Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Shape with greased fingers to form nests.
Add peanut chocolate candies for eggs.
Let stand until firm.
Dust bottom of nests lightly with confectioners sugar.
Makes 10 to 12 nests.

title: rhubarb meringue dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruit.
Reserve 3/4 cup of the pineapple juice.
In a saucepan, combine pineapple juice, brown sugar, butter, cinnamon, cloves and curry.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water.
Add to cooked mixture until thickens.
Pour over fruit and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 14 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies(preparation time: 20 minutes. bake time: 8 to 10 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cream butter flavor Crisco, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Beat in egg. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Mix into creamed mixture. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to cooling rack. Makes 2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken about 25 minutes, until done.
Cool, debone and remove skin.
Break up into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen and used later.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Mix cabbage and soup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and crackers and dot with butter. Cook until brown on top.

title: "baked" little new red potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scrape potatoes and quarter.
Put in plastic bag with oil and onion soup.
Shake until potatoes are well covered with dry onion soup.
Bake in oven until potatoes are soft and slightly brown.

title: baked italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet. Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese. Simmer slowly 2 hours. Add more water if necessary. Cook spaghetti until tender. Rinse with water; drain. Layer spaghetti in a large casserole alternately with sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: chicken on the grill
directions: Combine vinegar, water, butter and salt; heat until butter melts and salt dissolves.
Keep hot on grill.
Brush chicken on both sides with sauce.
Arrange chicken, bone side down, on grill 5 inches from medium coals.
Brush chicken generously with sauce every 10 to 15 minutes; turn.
Grill until golden brown and tender.

title: bacon cheese snacks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread on one loaf of party rye bread.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 32 snacks.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to package directions; let cool completely.

title: ratatouille
directions: Toss eggplant and zucchini with 1 teaspoon salt and let stand 30 minutes. Drain and dry on paper towels. Heat 1/4 to 1/2 cup olive oil in large skillet and lightly brown eggplant and zucchini slices. Remove and set aside. Add oil to skillet. Cook onions and green peppers until tender. (Stir in garlic.)
Put tomatoes on top. Cover and cook 5 minutes.

Gently stir in eggplant, zucchini and remaining seasonings. Simmer, covered, until desired tenderness. Uncover and cook 5 minutes, basting with juice from bottom of pan. Serve hot or cold. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry bars
directions: Pat mixture of First Layer into bottom of a 10 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: extraordinary good pot roast
directions: Brown meat and onions in a nonstick skillet on top of stove. Place roast in roasting pan with tight fitting lid.
Mix pepper, cloves, honey, sugar, lemon juice and salt together.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly and bake in 350° oven for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer on low for two hours.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well, taking care not to mash beans.
Place in covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May add or substitute Ranch Style beans, pintos or lima beans.

title: easy chicken casserole(if you can open a can, you can make this casserole.)
directions: This recipe is very rich.
After the first bite you will agree it is worth the extra calories.

title: quick and simple hamburger dip
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger with onion.
Drain fat.
Pour browned meat and onion in slow cooker.
Add garlic, salt tomato sauce, catsup, oregano, sugar, cream cheese and Parmesan.
Set cooker on low and serve when cream cheese has melted into mixture, approximately 1 hour.
Stir; taste and adjust seasonings.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Peel and remove seeds from cucumber.
Grate and drain excess moisture from cucumber.
Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Pour on sliced tomatoes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the margarine and corn syrup. Remove from heat and add soda, brown sugar, salt and butter or vanilla flavoring.
Stir well with 6 quarts of popped corn. Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In a bowl mix biscuit mix, cheese and pepper.
Stir in eggs just until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
