In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Using 2 tablespoons mixture for each round, cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Fold eggs in, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into a bowl and stir in brown sugar.
Add shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and remaining milk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes more and stir in pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with cream cheese or 7 Minute Frosting and decorate with chopped pecans.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan, sprinkle pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut. Drop cream cheese mixture by small spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: apple glazed pork chops
directions: You will need one Reynolds large oven bag.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in oven bag; place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Add onion soup mix, honey and apple juice to bag;
squeeze bag to blend in flour.
Add pork chops and apples to bag.
Turn bag to coat ingredients with sauce.
Arrange pork chops in even layer in bag with apples around pork chops.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake until pork chops are tender, 35 minutes.

title: mother's christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add lemon extract; mix.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and fruit (candied) by hand.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl mix sugar, flour and salt all together good, then add strawberries and stir until mixed good.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and distribute the 1 tablespoon of butter over berry mixture.
Place pie crust on top and seal edge.
Make slits in center and bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.

title: pauline's italian style chicken breast
directions: Brush or dip chicken in oil.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° in glass baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes (uncovered). Spoon some sauce over each piece.
Top with cheese.
Continue baking 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; simmer until onion is cooked and flavors are blended, 30 minutes to an hour.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water
until thread spins.
Then add peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until it turns a brownish gold.
Take from fire; add butter, salt and soda.
Pour into buttered pan or on buttered board to cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: chili with cornbread fiesta casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Stir in
chili. Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread corn muffin batter on the bottom of greased 2-quart casserole. Spoon chili mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven or until cornbread is done (an inserted toothpick comes out clean).
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and eggs together. Mix an additional 1 tablespoon of sugar with diced orange. Combine eggs with margarine, diced orange mixture and water. Combine with the ingredients that you mixed first. Fill greased and floured muffin cups about 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red hot apple salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiled water.
Add red hots.
Chill until it begins to set. Fold in apples, nuts and celery.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: grandma coy's curry pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and drain.
Combine salt and water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 5 hours. Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers. Heat to boiling and pack into sterile jars. Seal immediately!
(Do not have to use canner!)

title: country style doughnut puffs
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar; beat well.
Stir in milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture until well mixed.
Add melted butter.
Drop batter from teaspoon into deep Crisco heated to 375°.
Fry a few at a time, until browned, 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Combine remaining sugar and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Roll puffs in mixture to coat.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine ground cranberries and sugar. Chill overnight. The next morning, dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add to cranberries; fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Mix well. Pour into mold or serving bowl. Sprinkle with coconut. Chill until it is set. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: patti's party meatballs
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients.
Combine last 4 ingredients in saucepan; heat.
Stir until smooth.
Mix with other mixture.
Make into balls.
Place on pan or cookie sheet.
Put in freezer overnight.
Put in plastic bag; return to freezer.
Use as needed. When ready to cook, place in baking dish on cooked spaghetti with catsup over top (generously).
Bake 1 hour and serve.

title: beef stew - crock-pot or oven
directions: Cut carrots, potatoes and celery into chunks.
Mix all ingredients and put into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Take off for the day.
When you return, supper is ready.
Or put in pan and cover and put into oven at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: tomatoes delight
directions: Quarter tomatoes. Top with 1 slice of butter (1 teaspoon). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Nuke in microwave 10 seconds or until butter is melted and cheese is crystallized (lightly browned).

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and egg.
Melt shortening and add molasses, flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll in small balls and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: carrots and brown sugar
directions: Cook frozen carrots in microwave in 1-quart dish with small amount water.
Cook on High 5 minutes; drain water.
Toss margarine and brown sugar with carrots.
Return to microwave and cook additional 2 minutes.
Stir, let stand 1 minute, serve. Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken rolls almandine
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place pepper on end of chicken breast; roll up.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Coat chicken with flour.
Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Brush with combined 1/2 cup mayonnaise, milk, onions and ginger.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Combine remaining mayonnaise, pineapple juice and cheese.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over chicken. Top with red and green peppers if desired.	Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple delight coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Heat sugar and pineapple.
When cake is done, punch holes with end of wooden spoon into cake.
Pour hot sugar/pineapple mixture on cake.
Cook vanilla pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Let cool in fridge, then add Cool Whip and top with coconut.
Set overnight.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shred cheese.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
After cheese melts, remove from heat.
Slice potatoes and onions in baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Do not put milk or water in the cake mix; just eggs and oil. Using directions on box, add orange slices instead of water or milk.
Fix 3 layers.

title: jumbo corn burger
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beef with 2 slightly beaten eggs, tomato sauce, salt, dash of pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Spread half of mixture in 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients; spoon over meat loaf mixture.
Bake 1 hour. Serves 6.
Pretty garnished with tomato wedges.

title: spicy dip for vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream, spaghetti sauce mix, lemon peel and juice (chill).
Serve with vegetables.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put meat in saucepan and brown.
Drain any grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on a bun.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix sugar, milk and syrup and cook slowly until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture will hold its shape.
Turn out on board which has been dusted with confectioners sugar.
Shape into a long roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in chopped pecans; wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator to harden.
Slice with sharp knife.
Makes 1 pound.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk in a double boiler.
Then add broken pecans.
Beat with a wooden spoon until creamy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased plate and let cool for 15 minutes. Melt semi-sweet chocolate along with paraffin in a double boiler. Using a toothpick dip caramel pecan turtle in the chocolate.
Then put back on waxed paper; let cool.

title: gourmet pork medallions
directions: Cut pork tenderloin into 8 thin slices.
Gently pound to 1/4-inch thick medallions.
Mix flour with 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper.
Coat medallions with mixture.
In a skillet, saute medallions in 3 tablespoons of the butter until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet and keep warm in a 200° oven.
Add remaining butter to skillet and saute onion, scallops and mushrooms for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add Chablis and 1/4 of the heavy cream. Simmer until sauce is thickened.
Taste and add salt and pepper as needed.
Whip the remaining cream until stiff and fold into Hollandaise Sauce to make mousseline.

title: beef hash
directions: Saute onions in bacon fat until soft.
Add potatoes and beef. Add just enough milk to moisten and seasonings.
Mix well; cover skillet and simmer until both sides of hash are well browned. Slide hash onto hot platter and garnish with parsley.
Serves 5.

title: pink things
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into paper-lined muffin cups. Freeze.
Serve with whipped cream and cherry.
Yields 20.

title: mild chili
directions: Bring water to boil; add meat, chopped onion, garlic, salt, cumin and chili powder.
Simmer for hour, adding more water if needed.
Add soup and beans; simmer 30 minutes more, stirring often.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Remove large bones from salmon.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Fry in greased pan until brown on both sides.

title: tuna pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and complete crusts in usual way. Line bottom of pie pan with one crust. Cook and mash potatoes. Saute onions in the butter. Add onions, eggs, tuna, seasoning and milk to the potatoes.
Mix until light and fluffy. Fill pie shell with mixture.
Put on top crust.
Cut air holes. Bake until beautifully browned at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Combine all ingredients except dry noodles.
Place in covered casserole and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover, place noodles on top and bake 15 minutes.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1 or 2 tablespoons of cold water.
Mix all ingredients and chill in a 9 x 13 dish.

title: flavored mayo
directions: Put together in a blender and blend.
Keep in tight jar in the refrigerator for use on sandwiches, in casserole, for dips, etc.

title: chicken 'n stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in rectangular, flat baking dish.
Top chicken with cheese slices.
Mix soup, cream and wine together and pour over cheese slices.
Melt butter in a separate
pan and then add half of bag or 7 ounces of stuffing to the melted butter and toss.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take off stems and dice them up into very small pieces.
On outside of mushroom cap brush with very light vegetable oil.

Mix diced stem mixture with seasoned bread crumbs (approximately 1 cup), then add liquid mixture (only enough so it doesn't stick to your fingers; 1 cup hot water with 1 dissolved chicken bouillon cube).
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps until overflowing and rounding the edges.
Brush melted butter over the top of the caps or put 1/4 of pat of butter on top of the stuffing in cap.
Broil in oven until they turn brown, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Pour in floured sheet cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: tacos with homemade taco seasoning mix
directions: Peel and chop onions. Brown ground beef and onions till all pink is gone from meat. Drain grease. Add seasoning mix and 1/4 c water to meat. Stir in well and cook 5 min. more. (For more spicy tacos, use more seasoning.) Use taco meat in tortillas, taco shells, or bean beef burritos. Serve with your choice of toppings. You can also spread meat mixture in baking dish and cover with cornbread batter, top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cornbread is done. Add additional toppings when served. 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add spaghetti, turkey, 1/2 cup cheese and mushrooms.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Pour in pie shell.
Put strawberries on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cocoa, vanilla and butter together, then add your oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "crock-pot" barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in crock-pot. Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat at high speed with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread evenly in bottom of cooked and cooled pastry shell.
Arrange bananas on cream cheese layer.
Spread pie filling over banana slices.
Top with whipped cream and chill.
(I also use cherry pie filling.)

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake to mix well. Brush both sides of chicken with buttermilk.
Place in bag of crumbs and shake to coat.
Place chicken on broiler pan which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake at 500° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and salt. Stir and beat 1 minute.
Add 4 to 4 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Knead and let rise until double.
Make out into rolls. Cover and let rise.
Bake at 375°.

title: tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes; pour remaining combined ingredients over tomatoes.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce.

title: mexican dip(make 2 pans, this goes fast!)
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of lasagne dish.
Next, spread on top and finally sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Microwave for 5 minutes on High or bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Pass the tortilla chips!

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Sift flour and baking powder; mix into dough.
Add pecans last and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool.
Makes about 4 to 6 dozen.

title: greasepaint
directions: Be carefully in your selection.
Do not choose too round.
When once selected, give your entire thought to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle.
Others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience.
Sweeten with love; season with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion.
Serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and boil first 6 ingredients for 2 minutes. Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir and drop by tablespoons on wax paper. It doubles well.

title: crispy chicken supreme
directions: Place crushed Rice Krispies cereal in shallow dish or pan. Stir in paprika; set aside.
In a second shallow pan or dish, beat egg and mix in milk.
Add flour, salt and poultry seasoning.
Mix together until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter.
Coat with crushed cereal.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Recipe is for a large Texas sheet cake pan.
Press crescent roll dough onto bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and Hidden Valley dry dressing.
Spread over rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables over top of cream cheese. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Chill for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: colonial oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts (36).
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten cookies with a glass that has been dipped in water, then in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in pound cake pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Spread on a serving plate. Layer remaining ingredients according to your own taste.
Serve cold with chips.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite sizes and cover bottom of pan; layer the rest of the ingredients in the order given up to bacon.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and mix well.
Spread this over the salad like frosting.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and refrigerate overnight, up to 2 to 3 days.

title: simple spanish rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until rice mixture thickens.

title: pineapple cheese log
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except chilies and cheese. Fold in chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain well.
Add soups and onion.
Stir well.
Heat until hot.
Add peas, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Alternate layers of chilies and mixed cheeses.
Begin and end with chilies.
Mix flour with small amount of milk.
Beat in eggs; add the rest of the milk and pour over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well.
Cook corn according to package directions.
Combine broccoli, corn, 1 cup stuffing mix, soup, egg, butter and onion; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and remaining 1/4 cup stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fideo
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in saucepan.
In another large skillet brown vermicelli and garlic in oil.
Add ground meat, chili powder, tomatoes and 1 cup water to vermicelli.
Cover tightly and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cover and simmer another 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Combine dry cake mix with eggs and vegetable oil.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute, then remove to cooling rack.
Easy and delicious!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
broccoli with 1/4 cup chopped onion until tender. Drain and
place	in
a casserole dish.
Mix grated cheese and 1/4 cup onion; add soup mixed with 1/3 cup milk.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix and simmer for a few minutes until zucchini begins to soften slightly.
Chill and serve as pineapple to top cheesecake. Mix in salads or use in carrot cake.
It's unbelievable!

title: pea picking cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil thoroughly.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans (grease and flour pans).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Saute onion and pepper in a minimal amount of butter.
Heat soup; add onion, pepper and pimento.
Continue to heat this mixture thoroughly, then add mayonnaise.
If this mixture does not seem "pourable" add a small amount of milk to make so.

title: kentucky-like chicken coating
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter in plastic bag.
Melt butter.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted butter, then drop chicken (a couple of pieces at a time) in bag and shake until well coated.
Place in shallow baking pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit.
Heat to boil, then pour over Jell-O. Add cream cheese which has been softened and dissolved.
When cool, slowly add Cokes, then fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate several hours until it is set.

title: banana nut bread(my sister debbie's recipe)
directions: Mix well and bake in loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 to 2 loaves, depending on pans.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with juice and pudding mix.
Let set a few minutes, then fold in 8 ounces whipped topping and put into graham crust and top with 8 ounces whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: crisp-fried chicken
directions: Melt butter and dip chicken pieces into it.
Roll in crushed cereal, mixed with seasonings.
Place, skin side up, on shallow baking pan lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Do not cover or turn.

title: spinach ravioli(with pesto cream sauce)
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in saucepan whisk together pesto, sour cream, whipping cream and lemon zest. Heat slowly on low heat until heated through; stir constantly. Add tomatoes and gently flake in chicken of the sea albacore, salmon or light tuna; heat. Salt and pepper to taste. Fold ravioli into creamy seafood sauce. Evenly divide onto 2 plates. Top with pine nuts and parmesan cheese. Garnish with basil leaves.

title: cortney's congo bars
directions: Mix together; bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers and mix with sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add Certo.
Boil 1 minute.
Strain.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Add food coloring, red or green if you like.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil slowly on low heat for 1 hour.
Add your favorite flavor of jello.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place on bun half.
Toast in oven under broiler until bubbly.

title: fruit pie
directions: Beat condensed milk and lemon juice by hand until stiff. Fold in Cool Whip. Add drained fruit and coconut. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill. Makes 2 pies. Can be frozen.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Melt butter; mix in flour and walnuts.
Line a baking pan with mixture and bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Mix cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together and place on baked crust.
Put pudding mix and milk together in blender for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put on top of cheese layer.
Add Cool Whip on top of this.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party meatballs and franks
directions: Slice franks diagonally or prepare your favorite meatballs and brown them.
Pour selected sauce over them, heat and serve.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Put margarine, wine, ketchup, garlic and hot sauce in pan and cook very slowly until margarine is melted.
Put unpeeled shrimp in a shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over shrimp.
Thinly slice 2 lemons and place on top of shrimp.
Let shrimp marinate for 1 hour or more if needed.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with French bread to soak up sauce.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Put broccoli in bottom of baking dish.
Mix rice, soups, and Cheez Whiz.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate streusel coffee cake
directions: Prepare chocolate streusel; set aside. Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs; blend well on low speed. Stir in sour cream and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to batter. Blend well. Sprinkle 1 c. chocolate streusel into greased and floured 12 c. bundt pan. Spread one third of the batter (about 1 1/3 c.) in pan; sprinkle with half the remaining streusel (about 1 c.). Repeat layers, ending with batter on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate. Cool completely. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding and syrup well.
Gradually add the Pet milk and slightly beaten egg.
Add pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, until set and slightly cracked.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and pudding.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of wafers (in one layer), bananas (in one layer) and a layer of pudding.
Repeat, layering twice, ending with pudding. Chill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pudding mix to pineapple and mix well. Carefully fold in other ingredients. Chill.

title: piquant sauce for fish(serves 4)
directions: Place butter in a 1-cup glass measure.
Microwave on Medium-high (roast) for about 1 1/2 minutes, or until melted.
Add mustard, parsley flakes, garlic powder and lemon juice.
Pour sauce over fish to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, no special order, except almonds, parsley and paprika.
Put in large buttered casserole.
Top with chopped parsley, paprika and toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly.
Peas should be crisp.
Great for buffet crowd.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry-wine jelly
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven; bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 1 minute, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; stir in wine and pectin.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Quickly pour into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch layer of paraffin.
Cover with lids.
Yields 7 cups.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook livers, gizzards, and bouillon cubes in crock pot, filled with water, overnight on low. In the morning, prepare corn kits as directed on pkg. When cool crumble and mix with cooked rice in a large pan.

title: squash patties
directions: Place grated squash and onion in colander; sprinkle with salt. Let set until moisture is gone.
Add flour, meal, pepper, cheese and egg; mix well.
Form in patties; fry in hot oil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans and butter.
Mix thoroughly until flour is moistened.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 Cool Whip; spread this mixture over crust that has been cooled.
Pour 2 1/2 cups milk into bowl; add instant pudding and beat until thickened.
Pour over first mixture in crust and ice with remaining Cool Whip. Chill; cut into squares to serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Chill. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: buck eye balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Melt the chips and shortening, shape peanut butter mixture into balls and dip into chocolate, put on wax paper.
After dipped put in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spread undrained pineapple over filling.
Pour dry cake mix over pineapple.
Scatter chopped pecans over cake mix. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix, covering all the mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: grape-nuts
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl, except soda which should be added to milk just before adding the milk to the dry ingredients.
Last, add oleo and flavorings; mix well.
The thickness varies a little with your own whole wheat flour or store bought flour.
The dough should be fairly thick.
Put in pans and spread even with spoon. Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: asian chicken salad
directions: Heat dry skillet over low heat. Add almonds.
Cook, stirring until lightly browned and fragrant, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from skillet; reserve.
Whisk together canola oil, vinegar, soy sauce and ginger.
Combine spinach with chicken, oranges and scallions; toss with dressing.
Sprinkle with almonds and chow mein noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: pam's cole slaw
directions: Using a food processor, shred the cabbage and carrot.
Add the pineapple and dressing.
Mix well and chill.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Saute onions and bacon in the butter.
Add flour to make roux. Cook 3 to 5 minutes and do not burn.
Add clam stock and let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add chopped clams and potatoes.
Simmer additional 20 minutes.
Add cream.
Season with salt and white pepper.

title: barbecue turkey, beef, roast pork or chicken
directions: Lightly grease oblong pan or use foil.
Layer meat in pan. Cover meat with mixture and bake at 375°, covered.
Uncooked meat bake 2 hours.

title: christmas boiled cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add all remaining ingredients and beat well until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool or pour into pan and cool.
Then cut into squares.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from pan. Brown chopped head of cabbage in hamburger skillet. Layer cabbage, then hamburger in casserole dish.
Mix the soup with the Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: festive grasshopper cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl, stir cream cheese with a spoon until soft. Add dry pudding mix, dry milk powder, and water.
Mix well with whisk until blended.
Fold in mint extract.
Spread mixture evenly into piecrust.
In a small bowl, combine Cool Whip Lite and green food coloring.
Spread mixture evenly over cream cheese mixture. Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into 8 servings.
Diabetic:
1 1/2 starch/carbohydrate, 1 fat 1/2 meat.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar; mix pudding and milk in another bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
Then blend both mixtures together.
Crush cookies in blender or salad shooter. Line a large flower pot and layer Oreos and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with Oreos.
Refrigerate and serve with trowel.
Add artificial flower and gummy worms for decorations.

title: slow cooker fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in slow cooker on low, stirring to mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together. Add to cheese mixture gradually, mixing well after each addition. Stir in pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and season chicken breast and place in a long rectangular baking dish.
Lay onions on top of chicken, mix soups together and spread on top and add cheese.
Prepare stuffing as per directions and lay on
top (layer everything).
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan, sugar, cocoa, milk, butter, vanilla and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil; let boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat. Add pecans and peanut butter.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Mix in casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni-tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain thoroughly.
Rinse with cold water.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all soups and sauce in bowl. In crock-pot, layer ground beef, soup combinations, grated cheese, then Doritos.
Repeat process until crock-pot is full.
Turn on crock-pot until cheese is melted and bubbles.
Ready to eat!

title: biscuit-topped hamburger stew
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Spray large skillet and over medium high heat, cook beef and onion until thoroughly cooked. Drain. Add all remaining ingredients except biscuits, mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium low, cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Spoon into ungreased 2 or 2 1/2 quart baking dish. Separate dough into 5 biscuits, cut each in half. Arrange, cut side down around outside edge of hot mixture. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes or until casserole is bubbly and biscuits are deep golden brown.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add salt, flour and sugar.
Continue beating.
Add can of milk and quart of milk. Cook over boiling water until mixture coats the spoon.
Cool; add vanilla and cream.
Freeze in a crank type freezer.

title: easy spaghetti in the crock-pot
directions: Brown meat; saute onion and bell pepper.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook on low all day while you are at work.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Serve with hot French bread and green salad.

title: walnut eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat skillet, add oil and saute the eggplant until brown and soft.
Set aside.
In same skillet combine and simmer all other ingredients except the Mozzarella cheese for 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Carefully fold pudding and Cool Whip until blended.
Fold in pineapple with the syrup and the walnuts.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve as a side dish with meal or a dessert.

title: pumpkin cake in a jar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, adding sugar slowly. Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder salt, ground cloves, allspice, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and stir well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased canning jars, filling half full.
Place jars on cookie sheet.
Beat upright in preheated 325 degrees for about 45 minutes.
When done, remove one jar at a time from oven.
While still warm, place wax paper circle on the top end of the cake. Wipe sealing edge of jar.
Place lid on jar and close tightly with ring.
Turn jar upside down.
To serve:
Open jar, slide a knife around inside of the jar to loosen cake, and remove cake from jar. Warm cake in oven if desired.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice in a small saucepan. Set pineapple aside.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat; add water.
Cook until meat is almost done.
Add celery, onion, corn syrup and soy sauce.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: orange waldorf salad
directions: Chop up orange and apple into bite-size pieces. Combine all the ingredients, except the salad greens, in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate. Serve on salad greens.

title: patty cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar in mixer.
Pour into pan. Cover cake mix
batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Starts golden brown on top.

title: red earth cake
directions: Make paste of cocoa, red food coloring and coffee.
Cream sugar and shortening and add well beaten eggs.
Add flour in which soda and salt have been added.
Add milk, vanilla and paste.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured round cake pans.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat sweetened milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat oil, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add.
Make into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 13 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased muffin pan. Bake a 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon & baking soda. Using a fork, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stirring with fork, add enough buttermilk until mixture leaves sides of bowl

and soft dough forms. Turn dough onto floured surface; knead lightly until no longer sticky. Roll out 1/2 inch thick, cut with floured cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet with sides touching. Bake at 450° for 10-15 minutes or until light brown. Cool 5 minutes.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Using ogange juice and pineapple juice (makes about 1 1/2 cups juice).
Grind cranberries and pineapple; cover with sugar.

title: pizza steak sub
directions: Brown steak.
In another pan, brown onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Drain steak if necessary.
Add onions, peppers, mushrooms, pizza sauce and garlic salt to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes on low.
Put steak mixture on hoagie roll.
Top with cheese.
Quick and easy.
Tastes great.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in heavy skillet or kettle and boil about 12 minutes or until peanuts start popping,
then add 1 teaspoon soda.
Beat candy and pour into buttered pan.
Break into chunks when cold.

title: wedding punch
directions: Leave the corn husks on the corn.
Put the corn in microwave, with husks on, for about 6 or 7 minutes.
Take out at once.
It's ready to serve on table by taking the corn husks off when serving the corn.
The flavor and taste is so much better than cooking roasting ear corn the old fashioned way in water.
Butter corn while hot.
